#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:5932
#, no-c-format
msgid "Moodbar File Generation Script"
msgstr "Skript za ustvarjanje datoteke Moodbar"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5933
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here is a simple bash script that will add .mood files to your entire "
"collection. It adds mood files for all files matching the extensions in the "
"current directory and all subdirectories, so it's best run from the base of "
"your music directory."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj je preprost bash skript, ki bo dodal datoteke .mood vaši celotni "
"zbirki. Doda datoteke razpoloženja za vse datoteke, ki se ujemajo s "
"končnicami v trenutnem imeniku in vseh podimenikih, zato ga je najbolje "
"zagnati iz baze vašega glasbenega imenika."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:5935
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"#!/bin/bash\n"
" DIR=${1:-.}\n"
" LAST=~/.moodbar-lastreadsong\n"
" C_RET=0\n"
" control_c()        # run if user hits control-c\n"
" {\n"
"   echo \"\" &gt; \"$LAST\"\n"
"   echo \"Exiting...\"\n"
"   exit\n"
" }\n"
" if [ -e \"$LAST\" ]; then\n"
"   read filetodelete &lt; \"$LAST\"\n"
"   rm \"$filetodelete\" \"$LAST\"\n"
" fi\n"
" exec 9&lt; &lt;(find \"$DIR\" -type f -regextype posix-awk -iregex '.*\\."
"(mp3|ogg|flac|wma)') # you may need to add m4a and mp4\n"
" while read i\n"
" do\n"
"   TEMP=\"${i%.*}.mood\"\n"
"   OUTF=`echo \"$TEMP\" | sed 's#\\(.*\\)/\\([^,]*\\)#\\1/.\\2#'`\n"
"   trap 'control_c \"$OUTF\"' INT\n"
"   if [ ! -e \"$OUTF\" ]\n"
"     moodbar -o \"$OUTF\" \"$i\"\n"
"   fi\n"
" done &lt;&amp;9\n"
" exec 9&lt;&amp;-\n"
" exit $C_RET"
msgstr ""
"#!/bin/bash\n"
" DIR=${1:-.}\n"
" LAST=~/.moodbar-lastreadsong\n"
" C_RET=0\n"
" control_c()        # run if user hits control-c\n"
" {\n"
"   echo \"\" &gt; \"$LAST\"\n"
"   echo \"Exiting...\"\n"
"   exit\n"
" }\n"
" if [ -e \"$LAST\" ]; then\n"
"   read filetodelete &lt; \"$LAST\"\n"
"   rm \"$filetodelete\" \"$LAST\"\n"
" fi\n"
" exec 9&lt; &lt;(find \"$DIR\" -type f -regextype posix-awk -iregex '.*\\."
"(mp3|ogg|flac|wma)') # you may need to add m4a and mp4\n"
" while read i\n"
" do\n"
"   TEMP=\"${i%.*}.mood\"\n"
"   OUTF=`echo \"$TEMP\" | sed 's#\\(.*\\)/\\([^,]*\\)#\\1/.\\2#'`\n"
"   trap 'control_c \"$OUTF\"' INT\n"
"   if [ ! -e \"$OUTF\" ]\n"
"     moodbar -o \"$OUTF\" \"$i\"\n"
"   fi\n"
" done &lt;&amp;9\n"
" exec 9&lt;&amp;-\n"
" exit $C_RET"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5937
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Copy and paste the above into a text file named moodbar.sh in your music "
"directory and run the following commands:"
msgstr ""
"Kopirajte in prilepite zgoraj v besedilno datoteko z imenom moodbar.sh v "
"vašem glasbenem imeniku in zaženite naslednje ukaze:"

#. Tag: userinput
#: index.docbook:5939
#, no-c-format
msgid "cd /path/to/music bash moodbar.sh"
msgstr "cd /path/to/music bash moodbar.sh"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5944
#, no-c-format
msgid "Alternatively if the above does not work, you may try:"
msgstr "Če zgoraj navedeno ne deluje, lahko poskusite:"

#. Tag: userinput
#: index.docbook:5946
#, no-c-format
msgid "chmod +x moodbar.sh ./moodbar.sh"
msgstr "chmod +x moodbar.sh ./moodbar.sh"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5951
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This may take a very long time for large collections! Note that the moodbars "
"will not appear in &amarok; until &amarok; rescans the collection. The "
"generated <filename>mood</filename> files will be dotfiles (&ie;, prefixed "
"with a full stop), or hidden files - so keep this in mind if you can't find "
"any generated mood files."
msgstr ""
"Pri velikih zbirkah lahko to traja zelo dolgo! Upoštevajte, da vrstice "
"razpoloženja ne bodo prikazane v &amarok; dokler &amarok; ponovno skenira "
"zbirko. Ustvarjene datoteke <filename>mood</filename> bodo datoteke s pikami "
"(&ie; s predpono s piko) ali skrite datoteke – zato imejte to v mislih, če "
"ne najdete nobene ustvarjene datoteke razpoloženja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5953
#, no-c-format
msgid "Based on the above script, an alternative for multicore CPUs:"
msgstr "Na podlagi zgornjega skripta je alternativa za večjedrne procesorje:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:5955
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"#!/bin/bash\n"
" NUMCPU=\"$(grep ^processor /proc/cpuinfo | wc -l)\"\n"
" find . -type f -regextype posix-awk -iregex '.*\\.(mp3|ogg|flac|wma)' | "
"while read i ; do\n"
"        while [ `jobs -p | wc -l` -ge $NUMCPU ] ; do\n"
"                sleep 0.1\n"
"        done\n"
"        TEMP=\"${i%.*}.mood\"\n"
"        OUTF=`echo \"$TEMP\" | sed 's#\\(.*\\)/\\([^,]*\\)#\\1/.\\2#'`\n"
"        if [ ! -e \"$OUTF\" ] ; then\n"
"                moodbar -o \"$OUTF\" \"$i\" &amp;\n"
"        fi\n"
" done"
msgstr ""
"#!/bin/bash\n"
" NUMCPU=\"$(grep ^processor /proc/cpuinfo | wc -l)\"\n"
" find . -type f -regextype posix-awk -iregex '.*\\.(mp3|ogg|flac|wma)' | "
"while read i ; do\n"
"        while [ `jobs -p | wc -l` -ge $NUMCPU ] ; do\n"
"                sleep 0.1\n"
"        done\n"
"        TEMP=\"${i%.*}.mood\"\n"
"        OUTF=`echo \"$TEMP\" | sed 's#\\(.*\\)/\\([^,]*\\)#\\1/.\\2#'`\n"
"        if [ ! -e \"$OUTF\" ] ; then\n"
"                moodbar -o \"$OUTF\" \"$i\" &amp;\n"
"        fi\n"
" done"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:5958 index.docbook:6807
#, no-c-format
msgid "Troubleshooting"
msgstr "Odpravljanje težav"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5960
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the <guilabel>Moodbar</guilabel> executable gives you a <emphasis>bus "
"error</emphasis>, that almost always means it can't decode (or can't find) "
"your file. Take a look at the <link linkend=\"supported-filetypes"
"\">supported file types</link> below for ideas on which GStreamer plugins to "
"install. You can also try the command below to test whether GStreamer can "
"decode your file:<userinput>gst-launch-1.0 filesrc location=[file] ! "
"decodebin ! fakesink</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"Če vam izvršljiva datoteka <guilabel>Moodbar</guilabel> prikaže "
"<emphasis>napako vodila</emphasis>, to skoraj vedno pomeni, da ne more "
"dekodirati (ali ne najde) vaše datoteke. Spodaj si oglejte <link linkend="
"\"supported-filetypes\">podprte vrste datotek</link> za ideje o tem, katere "
"vtičnike GStreamer namestiti. Poskusite lahko tudi s spodnjim ukazom, da "
"preizkusite, ali lahko GStreamer dekodira vašo datoteko:<userinput>gst-"
"launch-1.0 filesrc location=[file] ! decodebin ! ponaredek</userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5961
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are using the ffmpeg plugin to decode mp3s, you may also receive "
"mysterious bus errors. The solution is to stop using the ffmpeg plugin, as "
"it is extremely buggy &mdash; use mad instead."
msgstr ""
"Če za dekodiranje datotek mp3 uporabljate vtičnik ffmpeg, lahko prejmete "
"tudi skrivnostne napake vodila. Rešitev je, da prenehate uporabljati vtičnik "
"ffmpeg, saj je zelo hrošč &mdash; namesto tega uporabite mad."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5962
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the <guilabel>Moodbar</guilabel> executable tells you that it can't find "
"an element &mdash; &ie;, it gives an error message like <screen>Could not "
"create element of type fftwspectrum, please install it.</screen>&mdash; that "
"usually means that you either don't have the required plugins installed (see "
"the plugin list <link linkend=\"supported-filetypes\">here</link>), or that "
"you didn't install the Moodbar package in the same prefix as GStreamer. If "
"libmoodbar.so and libgstdecodebin.so are not in the same directory, then "
"Moodbar is not installed in the same prefix as GStreamer. Please read the "
"INSTALL file for instructions on how to configure the moodbar package "
"correctly. Alternatively, <emphasis>if you know what you're doing,</"
"emphasis> it may be easier for you to take a look at the "
"<filename>GST_PLUGIN_PATH</filename> environment variable."
msgstr ""
"Če vam izvedljiva datoteka <guilabel>Moodbar</guilabel> sporoči, da ne najde "
"elementa &mdash; &ie;, prikaže sporočilo o napaki, kot je <screen>Ni bilo "
"mogoče ustvariti elementa vrste fftwspectrum, namestite ga.</screen>&mdash; "
"to običajno pomeni, da nimate nameščenih zahtevanih vtičnikov (glejte seznam "
"vtičnikov <link linkend=\"supported-filetypes\">tukaj</link>) ali da niste "
"namestili paketa Moodbar z isto predpono kot GStreamer. Če libmoodbar.so in "
"libgstdecodebin.so nista v istem imeniku, potem Moodbar ni nameščen v isti "
"predponi kot GStreamer. Preberite datoteko INSTALL za navodila, kako "
"pravilno konfigurirati paket moodbar. Druga možnost je, <emphasis>če veste, "
"kaj počnete,</emphasis> morda lažje, če si ogledate spremenljivko okolja "
"<filename>GST_PLUGIN_PATH</filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5963
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you're wondering why the <guilabel>Moodbar</guilabel> isn't working, "
"either not working at all or not working for a particular file, run the "
"command below, where [file] is a music file:<userinput>moodbar -o test.mood "
"[file]</userinput> To generate a test image preview, one can use the "
"commandː<userinput>gst-launch-1.0 filesrc location=[file] ! decodebin ! "
"audioconvert ! fftwspectrum ! moodbar height=50 max-width=300 ! pngenc ! "
"filesink location=mood.png</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"Če se sprašujete, zakaj <guilabel>vrstica razpoloženja</guilabel> ne deluje, "
"ali sploh ne deluje ali ne deluje za določeno datoteko, zaženite spodnji "
"ukaz, kjer je [datoteka] glasbena datoteka:<userinput> moodbar -o test.mood "
"[datoteka]</userinput> Za ustvarjanje predogleda testne slike lahko "
"uporabite ukazː<userinput>gst-launch-1.0 filesrc location=[datoteka]! "
"decodebin ! audioconvert ! fftwspekter! višina vrstice razpoloženja=50 max-"
"width=300 ! pngenc ! filesink location=mood.png</userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5964
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have multiple versions of GStreamer installed, make sure all of the "
"required plugins are installed <emphasis>for version 1.0.*</emphasis> -- "
"different versions <emphasis>cannot</emphasis> use each other's plugins."
msgstr ""
"Če imate nameščenih več različic GStreamerja, se prepričajte, da so "
"nameščeni vsi zahtevani vtičniki <emphasis>za različico 1.0.*</emphasis> -- "
"različne različice <emphasis>ne morejo</emphasis> uporabljati vtičnikov "
"druga druge."

