#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6063
#, no-c-format
msgid "Replay Gain"
msgstr "Replay Gain"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6064
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ReplayGain\">Replay gain</ulink> "
"will automatically adjust the volume of the currently played song, relative "
"to other songs, as determined by the person who encoded the audio file. To "
"enable replay gain, see <link linkend=\"settings-menu\">Settings menu</link>."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ReplayGain\">Replay gain</ulink> "
"samodejno prilagodi glasnost trenutno predvajane skladbe glede na druge "
"skladbe, kot določi oseba, ki je kodirala zvočna datoteka. Če želite "
"omogočiti pridobitev ponovnega predvajanja, glejte <link linkend=\"settings-"
"menu\">Meni z nastavitvami</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6066
#, no-c-format
msgid "To handle this, &amarok; relies on metadata embedded in the audio file:"
msgstr ""
"Za obravnavo tega &amarok; se opira na metapodatke, vdelane v zvočno "
"datoteko:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6069
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If no replay gain information is embedded, &amarok; will not adjust the "
"volume"
msgstr ""
"Če ni vdelan noben podatek o pridobitvi ponovnega predvajanja, &amarok; ne "
"bo prilagodil glasnosti"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6070
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If replay gain information is found, it will be written into &amarok;'s "
"database"
msgstr ""
"Če so najdene informacije o ojačanju ponovnega predvajanja, bodo zapisane v "
"&amarok; zbirko podatkov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6072
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"During playback, &amarok; will only look into its own database for this "
"information. Updates to the metadata of the file will not always get written "
"into the database during a collection update (&eg; replay gain is deleted "
"from file)."
msgstr ""
"Med predvajanjem &amarok; bo te informacije iskal samo v svoji bazi "
"podatkov. Posodobitve metapodatkov datoteke ne bodo vedno zapisane v bazo "
"podatkov med posodabljanjem zbirke (npr. pridobitev ponovnega predvajanja je "
"izbrisana iz datoteke)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6074
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This can lead to unexpected behavior: Songs from the same artist play at "
"different volume levels &etc;"
msgstr ""
"To lahko povzroči nepričakovano vedenje: Pesmi istega izvajalca se "
"predvajajo pri različnih glasnostih &etc;"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6076
#, no-c-format
msgid "Is replay gain being used?"
msgstr "Ali se uporablja replay gain?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6077
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To figure out if the volume problem is caused by replay gain or bad encoding:"
msgstr ""
"Da bi ugotovili, ali je težavo z glasnostjo povzročilo ojačenje ponovnega "
"predvajanja ali slabo kodiranje:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6080
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disable replay gain processing (see above)"
msgstr "Onemogoči ojačenje z obdelavo ponovnega predvajanja (glejte zgoraj)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6081
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start &amarok; in debug mode and search for gain- related output:"
msgstr ""
"Zaženi &amarok; v načinu za odpravljanje napak za iskanje ojačenega izhoda:"

#. Tag: command
#: index.docbook:6083
#, no-c-format
msgid "amarok -d --nofork | grep gain"
msgstr "amarok -d --nofork | grep gain"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6085
#, no-c-format
msgid "If replay gain is active for the played song, the output will be"
msgstr "Če je aktivno ponovno predvajanje za predvajano pesem, bo izhod"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6087
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using gain of -10.28 with relative peak of -1"
msgstr "Onemogoči obdelavo povečanja ponovitve (glejte zgoraj)"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6090
#, no-c-format
msgid "View replay gain information"
msgstr "Oglejte si informacije o ojačanju ponovnega predvajanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6091
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For .flac files, <quote>metaflac</quote> can be used to view embedded replay "
"gain data:"
msgstr ""
"Za datoteke .flac lahko <quote>metaflac</quote> uporabite za ogled vdelanih "
"podatkov o ojačanju ponovnega predvajanja:"

#. Tag: command
#: index.docbook:6093
#, no-c-format
msgid "metaflac --list Millencolin\\ -\\ Balanced\\ Boy.flac"
msgstr "metaflac --list Millencolin\\ -\\ Balanced\\ Boy.flac"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6095
#, no-c-format
msgid "Among other things, this will show something like this:"
msgstr "Med drugim bo to pokazalo nekaj takega:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6097
#, no-c-format
msgid "METADATA block #2"
msgstr "Oglejte si informacije o povečanju ponovitve"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6099
#, no-c-format
msgid "type: 4 (VORBIS_COMMENT)"
msgstr "type: 4 (VORBIS_COMMENT)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6101
#, no-c-format
msgid "is last: false"
msgstr "is last: false"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6103
#, no-c-format
msgid "length: 390"
msgstr "length: 390"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6105
#, no-c-format
msgid "vendor string: reference libFLAC 1.2.1 20070917"
msgstr "vendor string: reference libFLAC 1.2.1 20070917"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6107
#, no-c-format
msgid "comments: 14"
msgstr "comments: 14"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6109
#, no-c-format
msgid "comment[9]: REPLAYGAIN_REFERENCE_LOUDNESS=89.0 dB"
msgstr "comment[9]: REPLAYGAIN_REFERENCE_LOUDNESS=89.0 dB"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6111
#, no-c-format
msgid "comment[10]: REPLAYGAIN_TRACK_GAIN=-1.55 dB"
msgstr "comment[10]: REPLAYGAIN_TRACK_GAIN=-1.55 dB"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6113
#, no-c-format
msgid "comment[11]: REPLAYGAIN_TRACK_PEAK=0.75894165"
msgstr "comment[11]: REPLAYGAIN_TRACK_PEAK=0.75894165"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6115
#, no-c-format
msgid "comment[12]: REPLAYGAIN_ALBUM_GAIN=-4.19 dB"
msgstr "comment[12]: REPLAYGAIN_ALBUM_GAIN=-4.19 dB"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6117
#, no-c-format
msgid "comment[13]: REPLAYGAIN_ALBUM_PEAK=0.98712158"
msgstr "comment[13]: REPLAYGAIN_ALBUM_PEAK=0.98712158"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6119
#, no-c-format
msgid "To view this tracks information within the &amarok; database:"
msgstr "To view this tracks information within the &amarok; database:"

#. Tag: command
#: index.docbook:6121
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"select id, title, albumgain, albumpeakgain, trackgain, trackpeakgain from "
"tracks where title like &quot;Balanced%&quot;;"
msgstr ""
"select id, title, albumgain, albumpeakgain, trackgain, trackpeakgain from "
"tracks where title like &quot;Balanced%&quot;;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6123
#, no-c-format
msgid "Will show:"
msgstr "Will show:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6125 index.docbook:6129
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"+-------+------------------+-----------+---------------+-----------"
"+---------------+"
msgstr ""
"+-------+------------------+-----------+---------------+-----------"
"+---------------+"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6127
#, no-c-format
msgid "| id | title | albumgain | albumpeakgain | trackgain | trackpeakgain |"
msgstr "| id | title | albumgain | albumpeakgain | trackgain | trackpeakgain |"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6131
#, no-c-format
msgid "| 10459 | Balanced Boy | 0.53 | -5.60297 | 0.44 | -5.60297 |"
msgstr "| 10459 | Balanced Boy | 0.53 | -5.60297 | 0.44 | -5.60297 |"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6133
#, no-c-format
msgid "Note the difference in loudness levels"
msgstr "Upoštevajte razliko v stopnjah glasnosti"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6136
#, no-c-format
msgid "Delete replay gain information"
msgstr "Izbrišite informacije o povečanju ponovitve"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6137
#, no-c-format
msgid "First, delete the metadata from the file:"
msgstr "Najprej izbrišite metapodatke iz datoteke:"

#. Tag: command
#: index.docbook:6139
#, no-c-format
msgid "metaflac --remove-replay-gain Millencolin\\ -\\ Balanced\\ Boy.flac"
msgstr "metaflac --remove-replay-gain Millencolin\\ -\\ Balanced\\ Boy.flac"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6141
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After that, update your &amarok; collection. If it is still using replay "
"gain, update the database entry:"
msgstr ""
"Po tem posodobite &amarok; zbirka. Če še vedno uporablja pridobitev "
"ponovitve, posodobite vnos v zbirko podatkov:"

#. Tag: command
#: index.docbook:6143
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"update tracks set albumgain=-1,albumpeakgain=-1,trackgain=-1,"
"trackpeakgain=-1 where id=10459"
msgstr ""
"posodobi skladbe set albumgain=-1,albumpeakgain=-1,trackgain=-1,"
"trackpeakgain=-1 kjer id=10459"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6145
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Restart &amarok; and the log output should now show the updated values being "
"used."
msgstr ""
"Znova zaženi &amarok; izhod dnevnika pa bi moral zdaj prikazati uporabljene "
"posodobljene vrednosti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6147
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Feel free to try and mess with the values manually to improve volume levels."
msgstr "Lahko poskusite ročno spremeniti vrednosti, da izboljšate glasnost."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6151
#, no-c-format
msgid "Amarok on other platforms"
msgstr "Amarok na drugih platformah"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6152
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&amarok; is intended for the KDE desktop, but it works on other platforms as "
"well. Although it takes some effort, Amarok can run on these configurations:"
msgstr ""
"&amarok; je namenjen namizju KDE, deluje pa tudi na drugih platformah. "
"Čeprav je potrebno nekaj truda, lahko Amarok deluje v teh konfiguracijah:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6193
#, no-c-format
msgid "<link linkend=\"amarok-on-windows\">Windows</link>&nbsp;"
msgstr "<link linkend=\"amarok-on-windows\">Windows</link>&nbsp;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6212
#, no-c-format
msgid "<link linkend=\"amarok-on-mac-os-x\">OS X</link>&nbsp;"
msgstr "<link linkend=\"amarok-on-mac-os-x\">OS X</link>&nbsp;"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6218
#, no-c-format
msgid "Amarok on Non-KDE Desktops"
msgstr "Amarok na namizjih, ki niso KDE"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6219
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Although &amarok; is one the most well-known KDE applications, it can run on "
"other desktop environments too."
msgstr ""
"Čeprav &amarok; je ena najbolj znanih aplikacij KDE, lahko deluje tudi v "
"drugih namiznih okoljih."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6221
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section shows how &amarok; can be used on non-KDE &Linux; desktops. "
"These are examples; there may be more."
msgstr ""
"Ta razdelek prikazuje, kako &amarok; se lahko uporablja v ne-KDE &Linux; "
"namizni računalniki. To so primeri; lahko jih je več."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6223
#, no-c-format
msgid "GNOME"
msgstr "GNOME"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6237
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To configure the proxy for &amarok; on GNOME, modify and add this to "
"<filename>~/.kde/share/config/kioslaverc</filename>"
msgstr ""
"Če želite konfigurirati proxy za &amarok; v GNOME, spremenite in dodajte to "
"v <filename>~/.kde/share/config/kioslaverc</filename>"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:6239
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"[Proxy Settings][$i]\n"
"ProxyType=1\n"
"httpProxy=http://username:password@proxyserver:port/\n"
"httpsProxy=http://username:password@proxyserver:port/\n"
"ftpProxy=http://username:password@proxyserver:port/"
msgstr ""
"[Proxy Settings][$i]\n"
"ProxyType=1\n"
"httpProxy=http://username:password@proxyserver:port/\n"
"httpsProxy=http://username:password@proxyserver:port/\n"
"ftpProxy=http://username:password@proxyserver:port/"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6242
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enlightenment"
msgstr "Razsvetljenje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6256
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &amarok; systray icon does not work by default with E17. So, one should "
"disable the <guilabel>Show tray icon</guilabel> from <guilabel>General "
"Options</guilabel> in &amarok;'s preferences."
msgstr ""
"&amarok; ikona sistemske vrstice ne deluje privzeto z E17. Zato bi morali "
"onemogočiti <guilabel>Pokaži ikono pladnja</guilabel> v <guilabel>Splošnih "
"možnostih</guilabel> v nastavitvah &amarok;."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6259
#, no-c-format
msgid "XFCE"
msgstr "XFCE"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6273
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To launch &amarok; faster, enable <guilabel>Launch KDE services on startup</"
"guilabel> by going into <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</"
"guimenu><guisubmenu>Sessions and Startup</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Advanced</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> and checking the option."
msgstr ""
"Za zagon &amarok; hitreje omogočite <guilabel>Zagon storitev KDE ob zagonu</"
"guilabel> tako, da odprete <menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</"
"guimenu><guisubmenu>Seje in zagon</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Napredno</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice > in označite možnost."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6276
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fluxbox"
msgstr "Fluxbox"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6290
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If &amarok; is taking to long to load, add <userinput>exec kdeinit</"
"userinput> to <filename>~/.fluxbox/startup</filename>."
msgstr ""
"Če &amarok; nalaganje traja predolgo, dodajte <userinput>exec kdeinit</"
"userinput> v <filename>~/.fluxbox/startup</filename>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6293
#, no-c-format
msgid "LXDE"
msgstr "LXDE"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6307
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case &amarok; starts slowly in LXDE, you can add <guilabel>kdeinit</"
"guilabel> to the startup applications using the <guilabel>lxsession-edit</"
"guilabel> command."
msgstr ""
"V primeru, da &amarok; se v LXDE zažene počasi, lahko dodate "
"<guilabel>kdeinit</guilabel> zagonskim aplikacijam z ukazom "
"<guilabel>lxsession-edit</guilabel>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6311
#, no-c-format
msgid "Amarok on Windows"
msgstr "Amarok v sistemu Windows"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6312
#, no-c-format
msgid "This pages needs screenshots for the Amarok 2.8 version"
msgstr "Te strani potrebujejo posnetke zaslona za različico Amarok 2.8"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6314
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As you already know, a normal Windows install doesn't use KDE, so if you "
"want to install &amarok;, you can't just download the &amarok; package. You "
"must install a compatible compiler first. Here is described how to download, "
"install and run &amarok; in the Windows operating system."
msgstr ""
"Kot že veste, običajna namestitev sistema Windows ne uporablja KDE, zato, če "
"želite namestiti &amarok;, ne morete kar prenesti datoteke &amarok; paket. "
"Najprej morate namestiti združljiv prevajalnik. Tukaj je opisano, kako "
"prenesti, namestiti in zagnati &amarok; v operacijskem sistemu Windows."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6316
#, no-c-format
msgid "How to download"
msgstr "Kako prenesti"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6317
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you run into any difficulties, please visit the <ulink url=\"http://"
"community.kde.org/Amarok/GettingStarted/Download/Windows\">Amarok on Windows "
"wiki page</ulink> where the latest links will be kept updated. Otherwise, "
"use the latest at the following links:"
msgstr ""
"Če naletite na težave, obiščite <ulink url=\"http://community.kde.org/Amarok/"
"GettingStarted/Download/Windows\">wiki stran Amarok v sistemu Windows</"
"ulink>, kjer bodo shranjene najnovejše povezave posodobljeno. V nasprotnem "
"primeru uporabite najnovejše na naslednjih povezavah:"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6320
#, no-c-format
msgid "How to install"
msgstr "Kako namestiti"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6321
#, no-c-format
msgid "The installation is very simple, just run the downloaded .exe file."
msgstr "Namestitev je zelo preprosta, samo zaženite preneseno datoteko .exe."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6323
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you want to update be sure to remove your current install."
msgstr "Če želite posodobiti, odstranite trenutno namestitev."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6325
#, no-c-format
msgid "Step 1"
msgstr "Korak 1"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6326
#, no-c-format
msgid "First, review on the license terms."
msgstr "Najprej preglejte licenčne pogoje."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6342
#, no-c-format
msgid "Step 2"
msgstr "2. korak"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6343
#, no-c-format
msgid "Second, choose the install location."
msgstr "Drugič, izberite mesto namestitve."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6345
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to change the default location, select <guilabel>Browse...</"
"guilabel> and choose a new location."
msgstr ""
"Če želite spremeniti privzeto lokacijo, izberite <guilabel>Prebrskaj ...</"
"guilabel> in izberite novo lokacijo."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6361
#, no-c-format
msgid "Step 3"
msgstr "3. korak"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6362
#, no-c-format
msgid "Wait a few minutes while the installation finishes."
msgstr "Počakajte nekaj minut, da se namestitev konča."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6378
#, no-c-format
msgid "Step 4"
msgstr "4. korak"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6379
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the installation is done, dismiss the window with <guilabel>Close</"
"guilabel>. Your &amarok; installation has finished."
msgstr ""
"Ko je namestitev končana, zaprite okno z <guilabel>Zapri</guilabel>. Vaš "
"&amarok; namestitev je končana."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6396
#, no-c-format
msgid "Running Amarok"
msgstr "Poganjanje Amaroka"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6397
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the installation finishes, you'll find an &amarok; shortcut on your "
"desktop. To run &amarok;, just click the shortcut."
msgstr ""
"Ko je namestitev končana, boste našli &amarok; bližnjico na namizju. Če "
"želite zagnati &amarok;, preprosto kliknite bližnjico."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6401
#, no-c-format
msgid "Amarok on &MacOS; X"
msgstr "Amarok na &MacOS; X"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6402
#, no-c-format
msgid "Current Macports 2.1.3 only ships an outdated Amarok 2.6.0 version"
msgstr "Trenutni Macports 2.1.3 ponuja samo zastarelo različico Amarok 2.6.0"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6404
#, no-c-format
msgid "&amarok; can be installed and used on the &MacOS; X."
msgstr "&amarok; se lahko namesti in uporablja v sistemu &MacOS; X."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6406
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installation using MacPorts"
msgstr "Namestitev s pomočjo MacPorts"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6407
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To install &amarok; on &MacOS; X, first one needs to install MacPorts from "
"<ulink url=\"http://www.macports.org/install.php\">here</ulink>. Once "
"MacPorts is installed one needs to run the following command in the terminal:"
msgstr ""
"Če želite namestiti &amarok; na &MacOS; X, najprej morate namestiti MacPorts "
"iz <ulink url=\"http://www.macports.org/install.php\">tukaj</ulink>. Ko je "
"MacPort nameščen, morate v terminalu zagnati naslednji ukaz:"

#. Tag: userinput
#: index.docbook:6409
#, no-c-format
msgid "sudo port install amarok"
msgstr "vrata sudo namestite amarok"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6424
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <varname>port</varname> command will fetch all the dependencies, "
"compile, build and install them. This process may take quite some time, four "
"to five hours in a recent install."
msgstr ""
"Ukaz <varname>port</varname> bo pridobil vse odvisnosti, jih prevedel, "
"zgradil in namestil. Ta postopek lahko traja kar nekaj časa, štiri do pet ur "
"pri nedavni namestitvi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6428
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following screenshot shows &amarok; running on the &MacOS; X:"
msgstr ""
"Naslednji posnetek zaslona prikazuje &amarok; teče v sistemu &MacOS; X:"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6444
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other resources"
msgstr "Drugi viri"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6445
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you run into difficulties, there is a <ulink url=\"http://community.kde."
"org/Amarok/Development/OS_X\">troubleshooting page here</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Če naletite na težave, je tukaj <ulink url=\"http://community.kde.org/Amarok/"
"Development/OS_X\">stran za odpravljanje težav</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6450
#, no-c-format
msgid "Troubleshooting and Common Problems"
msgstr "Odpravljanje težav in pogoste težave"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6451
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you work through the procedures here, but don't have success, please come "
"into IRC (irc://irc.libera.chat/amarok), post on Discuss under <ulink url="
"\"https://discuss.kde.org/tag/amarok\">the Amarok category</ulink>, or write "
"to the <ulink url=\"https://mail.kde.org/mailman/listinfo/amarok\">Amarok "
"list</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Če delate skozi postopke tukaj, vendar niste uspešni, vstopite v IRC (irc://"
"irc.libera.chat/amarok), objavite na forumu <ulink url=\"https://discuss.kde."
"org/tag/amarok\">v kategoriji Amarok</ulink> ali pišite na <ulink url="
"\"https://mail.kde.org/mailman/listinfo/amarok\">seznam Amarok</ulink >."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6453
#, no-c-format
msgid "Problems installing"
msgstr "Težave pri namestitvi"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6454
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bad packaging"
msgstr "Slaba embalaža"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6455
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Occasionally, users will encounter bad packaging from the distributions; "
"either from the wrong version of a component being included, or some needful "
"part being left out. For some reason, this often happens with MySQL "
"dependencies. Bug reports in these cases should be made to your "
"distribution, not to bugs.kde.org."
msgstr ""
"Občasno bodo uporabniki naleteli na slabo embalažo distribucij; bodisi "
"zaradi napačne različice komponente, ki je bila vključena, bodisi zaradi "
"izpuščanja kakšnega potrebnega dela. Iz nekega razloga se to pogosto zgodi z "
"odvisnostmi MySQL. V teh primerih je treba poročila o napakah poslati vaši "
"distribuciji, ne na bugs.kde.org."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6458
#, no-c-format
msgid "Difficulties building from source"
msgstr "Težave pri gradnji iz vira"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6459
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For those who wish to help out by testing the newest &amarok; versions, a "
"local build is advised. Use this excellent guide: <ulink url=\"http://blogs."
"fsfe.org/myriam/2009/09/compiling-amarok-from-git-locally-full-summary/"
"\">Compiling Amarok from GIT Locally; a Full Summary</ulink>. Detailed "
"information about git can be found here: <ulink url=\"http://techbase.kde."
"org/Getting_Started/Sources/KDE_git-tutorial\">Techbase GIT Tutorial</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Za tiste, ki želijo pomagati s preizkušanjem najnovejših različic &amarok;a, "
"priporočamo lokalno gradnjo. Uporabite ta odličen vodnik: <ulink url="
"\"http://blogs.fsfe.org/myriam/2009/09/compiling-amarok-from-git-locally-"
"full-summary/\">Lokalno prevajanje Amaroka iz GIT; Celoten povzetek</ulink>. "
"Podrobne informacije o git lahko najdete tukaj: <ulink url=\"http://techbase."
"kde.org/Getting_Started/Sources/KDE_git-tutorial\">Vadnica Techbase GIT</"
"ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6461
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have built successfully before, and now are encountering errors, try "
"removing <filename>CMakeCache.txt</filename> and try again. If that still "
"errors out, remove the entire Build folder and build completely fresh."
msgstr ""
"Če ste že prej uspešno gradili in zdaj naletite na napake, poskusite "
"odstraniti <filename>CMakeCache.txt</filename> in poskusite znova. Če še "
"vedno pride do napake, odstranite celotno mapo Build in zgradite popolnoma "
"novo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6463
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The URL to pull from git has recently changed. Run <userinput><command>git "
"remote set-url origin git://anongit.kde.org/amarok</command></userinput> if "
"you still using the old URL. Please ping us if you find the old link in our "
"documents so we can update it everywhere."
msgstr ""
"URL za črpanje iz gita je bil nedavno spremenjen. Zaženite "
"<userinput><command>git remote set-url origin git://anongit.kde.org/amarok</"
"command></userinput>, če še vedno uporabljate stari URL. Če v naših "
"dokumentih najdete staro povezavo, nam pošljite ping, da jo bomo lahko "
"posodobili povsod."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6467
#, no-c-format
msgid "Problems starting up"
msgstr "Težave pri zagonu"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6468
#, no-c-format
msgid "Playlist errors"
msgstr "Napake seznama predvajanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6469
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The current playlist can occasionally get corrupt, which will prevent "
"&amarok; from starting. This can be fixed by simply removing the current "
"playlist file in the &amarok; directory, <filename>$HOME/.kde/share/apps/"
"amarok/current.xspf</filename> . Note that on some systems, this may be "
"<filename>.kde4</filename> rather than <filename>.kde</filename>."
msgstr ""
"Trenutni seznam predvajanja se lahko občasno poškoduje, kar bo &amarok;u "
"preprečilo; od začetka. To lahko popravite tako, da preprosto odstranite "
"trenutno datoteko seznama predvajanja v datoteki &amarok; imenik, <filename>"
"$HOME/.kde/share/apps/amarok/current.xspf</filename> . Upoštevajte, da je v "
"nekaterih sistemih to morda <filename>.kde4</filename> namesto <filename>."
"kde</filename>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6472
#, no-c-format
msgid "Database issues"
msgstr "Težave z bazo podatkov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6473
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the database is corrupt and this is preventing &amarok; from starting, "
"you can move the database to a backup location (or simply delete it). This "
"will cause &amarok; to rebuild the database from scratch. Move the <filename>"
"$HOME/.kde/share/apps/amarok/mysqle</filename> folder to a backup location "
"(such as <filename>$HOME/.kde/share/apps/amarok/mysqle~</filename>) and "
"restart &amarok;."
msgstr ""
"Če je baza podatkov poškodovana in to preprečuje &amarok; od začetka lahko "
"bazo podatkov premaknete na mesto varnostne kopije (ali jo preprosto "
"izbrišete). To bo povzročilo &amarok; obnoviti bazo podatkov iz nič. "
"Premaknite mapo <filename>$HOME/.kde/share/apps/amarok/mysqle</filename> na "
"mesto varnostne kopije (na primer <filename>$HOME/.kde/share/apps/amarok/"
"mysqle~</filename>) in znova zaženite &amarok;."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6476
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other issues and backing up settings"
msgstr "Druge težave in nastavitve varnostnega kopiranja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6477
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the above two items do not help, or you otherwise need to restore "
"&amarok; to a clean configuration, you can move to a backup location (or "
"delete) the &amarok; directory at <filename>$HOME/.kde/share/apps/amarok</"
"filename> and the &amarok; config files at <filename>$HOME/.kde/share/config/"
"amarok*</filename> (there may be two or three files matching this pattern). "
"Again, the directory may be <filename>.kde4</filename> rather than "
"<filename>.kde</filename>."
msgstr ""
"Če zgornja dva elementa ne pomagata ali morate kako drugače obnoviti "
"&amarok; v čisto konfiguracijo, lahko premaknete na mesto varnostne kopije "
"(ali izbrišete) &amarok; imenik na <filename>$HOME/.kde/share/apps/amarok</"
"filename> in &amarok; konfiguracijske datoteke na <filename>$HOME/.kde/share/"
"config/amarok*</filename> (lahko se dve ali tri datoteke ujemajo s tem "
"vzorcem). Imenik je lahko <filename>.kde4</filename> in ne <filename>.kde</"
"filename>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6481
#, no-c-format
msgid "Problems Scanning, Sorting files"
msgstr "Težave pri skeniranju, razvrščanju datotek"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6482
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&amarok; scans your music files on first startup, and will keep your "
"collection up-to-date automatically, if you chose "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guisubmenu>Configure Amarok</"
"guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Collection</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Watch folders "
"for changes</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"&amarok; skenira vaše glasbene datoteke ob prvem zagonu in bo vašo zbirko "
"samodejno posodabljal, če izberete <menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</"
"guimenu><guisubmenu>Konfiguriraj Amarok</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Zbirka</"
"guimenuitem ><guimenuitem>Oglejte si mape za spremembe</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6484
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you don't want &amarok; scanning for changes, uncheck that, and use "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</guimenu><guimenuitem>Update Collection</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> whenever you make changes to your collection."
msgstr ""
"Če ne želite &amarok; iskanje sprememb, počistite to polje in uporabite "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Orodja</guimenu><guimenuitem>Posodobi zbirko</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> vsakič, ko spremenite svojo zbirko."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6486
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"More about <link linkend=\"collection-scanning\">Amarok collection scanning "
"here</link>."
msgstr ""
"Več o <link linkend=\"collection-scanning\">skeniranju zbirke Amarok tukaj</"
"link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6488
#, no-c-format
msgid "Corrupt tags"
msgstr "Poškodovane oznake"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6489
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some folks notice that &amarok; seems to be missing some files. One of the "
"causes can be corrupt tags, which you can check using the tagging "
"application <ulink url=\"http://kid3.sourceforge.net/\">kid3</ulink>. More "
"about tagging <link linkend=\"tag-editor\">here</link>."
msgstr ""
"Nekateri opazijo, da &amarok; zdi se, da manjka nekaj datotek. Eden od "
"vzrokov so lahko poškodovane oznake, ki jih lahko preverite z aplikacijo za "
"označevanje <ulink url=\"http://kid3.sourceforge.net/\">kid3</ulink>. Več o "
"označevanju <link linkend=\"tag-editor\">tukaj</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6491
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To find the bad file(s), run <varname>amarokcollectionscanner</varname> from "
"the console. Details <ulink url=\"http://community.kde.org/Amarok/"
"Development/BatchMode\">here</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Če želite najti napačne datoteke, zaženite <varname>amarokcollectionscanner</"
"varname> s konzole. Podrobnosti <ulink url=\"http://community.kde.org/Amarok/"
"Development/BatchMode\">tukaj</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6494
#, no-c-format
msgid "Inability to write tags"
msgstr "Nezmožnost pisanja oznak"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6495
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If &amarok; is not saving changes to tags, you may have permissions "
"problems. Ensure that your user has write permissions to your music. For "
"example, <userinput>chown -R youruser Music/</userinput> to change ownership "
"to your user, or <userinput>chmod -R +w Music/</userinput> to add write "
"permissions to the owner."
msgstr ""
"Če &amarok; ne shranjuje sprememb oznak, imate morda težave z dovoljenji. "
"Prepričajte se, da ima vaš uporabnik dovoljenja za pisanje vaše glasbe. Na "
"primer, <userinput>chown -R youruser Music/</userinput>, da spremenite "
"lastništvo na svojega uporabnika, ali <userinput>chmod -R +w Music/</"
"userinput>, da dodate dovoljenja za pisanje lastniku."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6498
#, no-c-format
msgid "Incorrect Sorting (Various Artists)"
msgstr "Nepravilno razvrščanje (različni izvajalci)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6499
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sometimes people report that tracks are in Various Artists when they should "
"not be, or are sorted into <quote>Unknown Album.</quote> What separates "
"Various Artists albums and tracks and albums sorted under their artists is "
"the Album Artist tag. When you click <guilabel>Show under Various Artists</"
"guilabel> in the context (right-click) menu, that tag will be emptied if it "
"is filled. The opposite happens to a file in Various Artists when you choose "
"<guilabel>Do not show under Various Artists</guilabel>, but the Album Artist "
"tag will be auto-filled from the Artist tag."
msgstr ""
"Včasih ljudje poročajo, da so skladbe v Različni izvajalci, čeprav ne bi "
"smele biti, ali pa so razvrščene v <quote>Neznani album.</quote> Kar ločuje "
"albume Različnih izvajalcev ter skladbe in albume, razvrščene pod njihovimi "
"izvajalci, je oznaka Izvajalec albuma. Ko kliknete <guilabel>Prikaži pod "
"različnimi izvajalci</guilabel> v kontekstnem meniju (desni klik), bo ta "
"oznaka izpraznjena, če je izpolnjena. Nasprotno se zgodi z datoteko v "
"Različni izvajalci, ko izberete <guilabel>Ne prikaži pod Različni izvajalci</"
"guilabel>, vendar bo oznaka Izvajalec albuma samodejno izpolnjena iz oznake "
"Izvajalec."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6501
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If there is no Album tag, and no Album Artist tag, &amarok; will put the "
"track into Unknown Album in Various Artists. If you want them sorted "
"otherwise, tag them the way you want them sorted. If you don't know some of "
"the information, try out the new <emphasis>MusicBrainz</emphasis> function "
"in the tag editor, or use a tagging application."
msgstr ""
"Če ni oznake albuma in oznake izvajalca albuma, &amarok; bo skladbo uvrstil "
"v Unknown Album v Various Artists. Če želite, da so razvrščeni drugače, jih "
"označite tako, kot želite. Če nekaterih informacij ne poznate, preizkusite "
"novo funkcijo <emphasis>MusicBrainz</emphasis> v urejevalniku oznak ali "
"uporabite aplikacijo za označevanje."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6504
#, no-c-format
msgid "Duplicate Tracks"
msgstr "Podvojene skladbe"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6505
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sometimes Amarok pops up following dialog during (perhaps initial) "
"collection scan:"
msgstr ""
"Včasih Amarok prikaže naslednje pogovorno okno med (morda začetnim) "
"skeniranjem zbirke:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6520
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This most probably means that an identical file ended up twice in your "
"collection at different places. You can use Amarok's File Browser to check "
"the files individually, <guilabel>usual action is to remove one of the "
"duplicate files</guilabel>. If you are sure that the tracks are not (or "
"shouldn't be) duplicates, there may be several reasons why &amarok; thinks "
"they are:"
msgstr ""
"To najverjetneje pomeni, da je enaka datoteka dvakrat končala v vaši zbirki "
"na različnih mestih. Za preverjanje datotek posamezno lahko uporabite "
"Amarokov brskalnik datotek, <guilabel>običajno dejanje je odstranitev ene od "
"podvojenih datotek</guilabel>. Če ste prepričani, da skladbe niso (ali ne bi "
"smele biti) dvojniki, obstaja več razlogov, zakaj &amarok; misli, da so:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6523
#, no-c-format
msgid "The files are bit-by-bit identical"
msgstr "Datoteke so po bitih enake"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6524
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use for example <varname>md5sum</varname> command to verify that"
msgstr ""
"Uporabite lahko na primer ukaz <varname>md5sum</varname>, da to preverite"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6525
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can edit metadata of one of the files from within &amarok; File browser "
"to differentiate them somehow, perhaps by editing (album) artist, year, "
"composer or a comment"
msgstr ""
"Metapodatke ene od datotek lahko urejate znotraj &amarok; Datotečni "
"brskalnik, da jih nekako razlikuje, morda z urejanjem izvajalca (albuma), "
"letnika, skladatelja ali komentarja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6528
#, no-c-format
msgid "The files have the same Amarok AFT unique id"
msgstr "Datoteke imajo enak edinstveni ID Amarok AFT"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6529
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is often a result of running amarok_afttagger and then creating "
"multiple copies of a tagged file; tag reader such as Kid3 or MP3Diags can be "
"used to verify this, look for <varname>Amarok 2 AFTv1</varname> string in "
"tags"
msgstr ""
"To je pogosto posledica zagona amarok_afttagger in nato ustvarjanja več "
"kopij označene datoteke; za preverjanje tega lahko uporabite bralnik oznak, "
"kot je Kid3 ali MP3Diags, poiščite niz <varname>Amarok 2 AFTv1</varname> v "
"oznakah"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6530
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use <varname>amarok_afttagger</varname> command-line utility to "
"reset unique id of one of the tracks: <userinput>amarok_afttagger --newid --"
"verbose path/to/one/of/the/tracks.mp3</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"Za ponastavitev edinstvenega ID-ja ene od skladb lahko uporabite "
"<varname>amarok_afttagger</varname> pripomoček ukazne vrstice: "
"<userinput>amarok_afttagger --newid --verbose path/to/one/of/the/tracks.mp3</"
"userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6531
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can remove the unique id from one of the tracks, loosing "
"the track-even-if-changed-from-outside functionality: "
"<userinput>amarok_afttagger --delete --verbose path/to/one/of/the/tracks."
"mp3</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"Druga možnost je, da odstranite edinstveni ID iz ene od skladb, s čimer "
"izgubite funkcionalnost sledi-tudi če-je-spremenjena-od-zunaj: "
"<userinput>amarok_afttagger --delete --verbose path/to/one/of/the/tracks ."
"mp3</userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6534
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"(for Amarok before <ulink url=\"http://commits.kde.org/"
"amarok/216c18bdaf1\">v2.7.0-96-g216c18b</ulink>) The files have the same "
"MusicBrainz id"
msgstr ""
"(za Amarok pred <ulink url=\"http://commits.kde.org/"
"amarok/216c18bdaf1\">v2.7.0-96-g216c18b</ulink>) Datoteke imajo enak "
"MusicBrainz ID"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6535
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Released versions up to &amarok; 2.7 treated MusizBrainz id embedded in tags "
"(filled in by MusicBrainz-enabled tagger such as Picard) as unique "
"identifiers of tracks. However, MusicBrainz changed the semantics of the id "
"to mean <quote>recording id</quote> since it was originally implemented in "
"&amarok;, which means that you may get false duplicates for example for "
"tracks that appear on the original album and the Best of one. See <emphasis "
"role=\"strikethrough\"><ulink url=\"https://bugs.kde.org/show_bug.cgi?"
"id=315329\">bug #315329</ulink></emphasis> for more info"
msgstr ""
"Izdane različice do &amarok; 2.7 je ID MusizBrainz, vdelan v oznake "
"(izpolnjen z označevalcem, ki podpira MusicBrainz, kot je Picard), "
"obravnaval kot edinstvene identifikatorje skladb. Vendar je MusicBrainz "
"spremenil semantiko id-ja v pomen <quote>id posnetka</quote>, saj je bil "
"prvotno implementiran v &amarok;, kar pomeni, da lahko dobite lažne dvojnike "
"na primer za skladbe, ki se pojavljajo na izvirnem albumu in Best enega. Za "
"več informacij glejte <emphasis role=\"strikethrough\"><ulink url=\"https://"
"bugs.kde.org/show_bug.cgi?id=315329\">hrošč #315329</ulink></emphasis>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6536
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use any advanced tag reader to verify this (look for "
"<varname>MusicBrainz</varname> string in tags) and to remove the MusicBrainz "
"id from one of the tracks"
msgstr ""
"Uporabite lahko kateri koli napredni bralnik oznak, da to preverite (v "
"oznakah poiščite niz <varname>MusicBrainz</varname>) in odstranite ID "
"MusicBrainz iz ene od skladb"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6537
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As an alternative solution, you can use <varname>amarok_afttagger</varname> "
"to add &amarok; AFT id to one of the tracks because &amarok; will then "
"prefer its own id rather than the MusicBrainz one: "
"<userinput>amarok_afttagger --newid --verbose path/to/one/of/the/tracks.mp3</"
"userinput>"
msgstr ""
"Kot alternativno rešitev lahko uporabite <varname>amarok_afttagger</"
"varname>, da dodate &amarok; AFT ID za eno od skladb, ker &amarok; bo potem "
"raje izbral lasten ID kot ID MusicBrainz: <userinput>amarok_afttagger --"
"newid --verbose path/to/one/of/the/tracks.mp3</userinput>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6543
#, no-c-format
msgid "Problems playing files"
msgstr "Težave pri predvajanju datotek"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6544
#, no-c-format
msgid "Amarok skips over tracks, or appears to play them without sound"
msgstr "Amarok preskakuje skladbe ali pa se zdi, da jih predvaja brez zvoka"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6545
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the files you are attempting to play are in mp3 format, please see "
"instructions for enabling mp3 support on your distro, <link linkend=\"what-"
"media-types-does-amarok-support\">here</link>. Note that one piece of "
"software being able to play mp3s on your system does not necessarily mean "
"&amarok; has had the required codecs installed."
msgstr ""
"Če so datoteke, ki jih poskušate predvajati, v formatu mp3, si oglejte "
"navodila za omogočanje podpore za mp3 v vaši distribuciji, <link linkend="
"\"what-media-types-does-amarok-support\">tukaj</link>. Upoštevajte, da en "
"del programske opreme, ki lahko predvaja mp3 na vašem sistemu, ne pomeni "
"nujno, da &amarok; je imel nameščene potrebne kodeke."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6548
#, no-c-format
msgid "No sound, or bad sound"
msgstr "Ni zvoka ali pa je zvok slab"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6549
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For more general sound issues, first check what Phonon backend you are using "
"in <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guisubmenu>Configure Amarok</"
"guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Playback</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Configure Phonon</"
"guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Backend</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Consider "
"switching to a different backend; VLC and GStreamer backends should be "
"available from your distribution. Both the Gstreamer or VLC backends are "
"recommended, if your distribution is still shipping other backends do not "
"use them."
msgstr ""
"Za bolj splošne težave z zvokom najprej preverite, katero zaledje Phonon "
"uporabljate v <menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</"
"guimenu><guisubmenu>Konfiguracija Amaroka</"
"guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Predvajanje</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Konfiguracija "
"Phonona</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Zaledje</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. "
"Razmislite o prehodu na drugo zaledje; Zaledja VLC in GStreamer bi morala "
"biti na voljo v vaši distribuciji. Priporočljiva sta oba ozadja Gstreamer "
"ali VLC; če vaša distribucija še vedno pošilja druga ozadja, jih ne "
"uporabljajte."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6551
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Also check whether the backend standalone software can play the files "
"correctly; if not this is an issue with that software and you may find "
"information in their help files. In other words, can Gstreamer or VLC play "
"the same file? Will it play in <ulink url=\"help:/dragonplayer\">Dragon</"
"ulink>, which also uses phonon?"
msgstr ""
"Preverite tudi, ali lahko zaledna samostojna programska oprema pravilno "
"predvaja datoteke; če ne, je to težava s to programsko opremo in boste morda "
"našli informacije v njihovih datotekah pomoči. Z drugimi besedami, ali lahko "
"Gstreamer ali VLC predvaja isto datoteko? Ali se bo igral v <ulink url="
"\"help:/dragonplayer\">Dragon</ulink>, ki prav tako uporablja fonon?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6553
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If it seems to be a PulseAudio problem, and you want to provide a log to the "
"PulseAudio developers, the troubleshooting page is <ulink url=\"https://wiki."
"ubuntu.com/PulseAudio/Log\">here</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Če se zdi, da je težava v PulseAudio in želite razvijalcem PulseAudio "
"posredovati dnevnik, je stran za odpravljanje težav <ulink url=\"https://"
"wiki.ubuntu.com/PulseAudio/Log\">tukaj</ulink> ."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6557
#, no-c-format
msgid "Problems with collections on iPod &etc;"
msgstr "Težave z zbirkami na iPodu &etc;"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6558
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Amarok show no cover-images or images are lost when transferring to device"
msgstr ""
"Amarok ne prikaže nobenih naslovnih slik ali pa se slike izgubijo pri "
"prenosu v napravo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6559
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most likely the wrong version of libgpod4 is installed. On Debian and it's "
"derivatives like Kubuntu the default is libgpod4-nogtk, which comes without "
"support for covers. Simply install the variant libgpod4: <userinput>sudo apt-"
"get install libgpod4</userinput> The package libgpod4-nogtk can then be "
"removed without problem. From Kubuntu Quantal Quetzal on (released as 12.10) "
"this package has been removed and the default is libgpod4."
msgstr ""
"Najverjetneje je nameščena napačna različica libgpod4. V Debianu in njegovih "
"izpeljankah, kot je Kubuntu, je privzeta nastavitev libgpod4-nogtk, ki je "
"brez podpore za naslovnice. Preprosto namestite različico libgpod4: "
"<userinput>sudo apt-get install libgpod4</userinput> Paket libgpod4-nogtk "
"lahko nato brez težav odstranite. Od Kubuntu Quantal Quetzal naprej (izdan "
"kot 12.10) je bil ta paket odstranjen in privzeti je libgpod4."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6563
#, no-c-format
msgid "Crashes and bugs"
msgstr "Zrušitve in napake"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6565
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"How to run &amarok; from the command line: <userinput>amarok --debug --"
"nofork</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"Kako zagnati &amarok; iz ukazne vrstice: <userinput>amarok --debug --nofork</"
"userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6566
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&amarok; crashes, but <guilabel>Dr. Konqi</guilabel> doesn't pop up &mdash; "
"run in <guilabel>gdb</guilabel> with the following command: <userinput>gdb --"
"args amarok --debug --nofork</userinput> In <guilabel>gdb's</guilabel> "
"console, type <varname>run</varname> to start &amarok;, reproduce the crash, "
"and then in <guilabel>gdb</guilabel> type <varname>thread apply all bt</"
"varname> to generate the backtrace."
msgstr ""
"&amarok; se sesuje, vendar <guilabel>Dr. Konqi</guilabel> se ne prikaže "
"&mdash; zaženite v <guilabel>gdb</guilabel> z naslednjim ukazom: "
"<userinput>gdb --args amarok --debug --nofork</userinput> V konzolo "
"<guilabel>gdb</guilabel> vnesite <varname>run</varname>, da zaženete "
"&amarok;, ponovite sesutje in nato v <guilabel>gdb</guilabel> vnesite "
"<varname>thread apply all bt</varname>, da ustvarite povratno sled."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6567
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Filing bugs: If triggered, <guilabel>Dr. Konqi</guilabel> will provide an "
"option to report a bug and do most of the work for you. If not, you will "
"need to submit the bug manually at <ulink url=\"http://bugs.kde.org/"
"enter_bug.cgi?product=amarok\"> bugs.kde.org</ulink>. For crash bugs, paste "
"the backtrace from <guilabel>gdb</guilabel> as a comment."
msgstr ""
"Prijava hroščev: Če se sproži, <guilabel>Dr. Konqi</guilabel> bo ponudil "
"možnost prijave hrošča in opravil večino dela namesto vas. Če ne, boste "
"morali napako ročno predložiti na <ulink url=\"http://bugs.kde.org/enter_bug."
"cgi?product=amarok\"> bugs.kde.org</ulink>. Za napake pri zrušitvah "
"prilepite povratno sled iz <guilabel>gdb</guilabel> kot komentar."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6568
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"How to get personal support with problems: <ulink url=\"irc://irc.libera."
"chat/#amarok\">IRC</ulink> (#amarok on Libera Chat IRC), <ulink url="
"\"https://discuss.kde.org/tag/amarok\">Discuss</ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://"
"mail.kde.org/mailman/listinfo/amarok\">Mailing list</ulink>"
msgstr ""
"Kako pridobiti osebno podporo pri težavah: <ulink url=\"irc://irc.libera."
"chat/#amarok\">IRC</ulink> (#amarok na Libera Chat IRC), <ulink url="
"\"https://discuss.kde.org/tag/amarok\">Forum</ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://"
"mail.kde.org/mailman/listinfo/amarok\">Poštni seznam</ulink>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6572
#, no-c-format
msgid "Frequently Asked Questions"
msgstr "Pogosto zastavljena vprašanja"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6573
#, no-c-format
msgid "What is Amarok?"
msgstr "Kaj je Amarok?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6574
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&amarok; is an audio player. More information can be found in <link linkend="
"\"amarok-menu\">a summary of its features</link> and the <ulink url=\"http://"
"amarok.kde.org/en/screenshots\">screenshot gallery</ulink>. To get started "
"using &amarok;, see the <link linkend=\"quick-start-guide\">Quick Start "
"Guide</link>. The &amarok; Handbook is <link linkend=\"introduction\">here</"
"link>."
msgstr ""
"&amarok; je predvajalnik zvoka. Več informacij lahko najdete v <link linkend="
"\"amarok-menu\">povzetku njegovih funkcij</link> in <ulink url=\"http://"
"amarok.kde.org/en/screenshots\">galeriji posnetkov zaslona</ulink>. Če "
"želite začeti uporabljati &amarok;, glejte <link linkend=\"quick-start-guide"
"\">Vodnik za hiter začetek</link>. &amarok; Priročnik je <link linkend="
"\"introduction\">tukaj</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6577
#, no-c-format
msgid "What are the differences between Amarok 2 and the previous versions?"
msgstr "Kakšne so razlike med Amarokom 2 in prejšnjimi različicami?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6578
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&amarok; 2 is a nearly complete code-rewrite so the codebase has little to "
"do with &amarok; 1.4. If you are missing a feature, please file a wish in "
"<ulink url=\"http://bugs.kde.org\">Bugzilla</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"&amarok; 2 je skoraj popolno prepisano kodo, tako da kodna baza nima veliko "
"skupnega z &amarok; 1.4. Če vam manjka funkcija, vnesite željo v <ulink url="
"\"http://bugs.kde.org\">Bugzilla</ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6580
#, no-c-format
msgid "Here you have a short list of some new features:"
msgstr "Tukaj imate kratek seznam nekaterih novih funkcij:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6583
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Maybe the biggest new feature is the <emphasis>Service Framework</emphasis>, "
"which integrates networked music sources directly into &amarok;. This "
"includes online music stores, media servers, Web music lockers, and more. "
"Thanks to it you'll get easy access to music provided by "
"<emphasis>Magnatune</emphasis>, <emphasis>Jamendo</emphasis>, <emphasis>Last."
"fm</emphasis>, <emphasis>MP3Tunes Locker</emphasis>, <guilabel>Ampache</"
"guilabel> and many others. Expect more big (and small) names to join during "
"the 2.x lifecycle. See <link linkend=\"internet\">Internet Media Sources</"
"link> for more."
msgstr ""
"Morda največja novost je <emphasis>Service Framework</emphasis>, ki "
"integrira omrežne glasbene vire neposredno v &amarok;. To vključuje spletne "
"glasbene trgovine, medijske strežnike, spletne glasbene omarice in drugo. "
"Zahvaljujoč temu boste imeli enostaven dostop do glasbe, ki jo ponujajo "
"<emphasis>Magnatune</emphasis>, <emphasis>Jamendo</emphasis>, <emphasis>Last."
"fm</emphasis>, <emphasis>MP3Tunes Locker</emphasis> >, <guilabel>Ampache</"
"guilabel> in mnogi drugi. Pričakujte več velikih (in majhnih) imen, ki se "
"bodo pridružila v življenjskem ciklu 2.x. Za več glejte <link linkend="
"\"internet\">Internet Media Sources</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6584
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Another exciting feature is the <guilabel>Context</guilabel> pane, occupying "
"the central place of the &amarok;'s window, replacing the old "
"<emphasis>Context Browser</emphasis> from the 1.x series. It displays "
"contextual information about the music you play, like the album cover, track "
"rating, labels, lyrics, artist information, related songs and artists, "
"guitar and bass tabs and others. Thanks to the Plasma technology it uses, "
"the <guilabel>Context</guilabel> pane can provide very rich content, like "
"AJAX, video and animations, all in an eye-catching fashion. More about the "
"<link linkend=\"the-context-pane\">Context pane</link>."
msgstr ""
"Druga vznemirljiva funkcija je podokno <guilabel>Kontekst</guilabel>, ki "
"zaseda osrednje mesto okna &amarok; in nadomešča stari <emphasis>Kontekstni "
"brskalnik</emphasis> iz serije 1.x. Prikazuje kontekstualne informacije o "
"glasbi, ki jo predvajate, na primer naslovnico albuma, oceno skladbe, "
"založbe, besedila, podatke o izvajalcu, povezane pesmi in izvajalce, zavihke "
"za kitaro in bas in drugo. Zahvaljujoč tehnologiji Plasma, ki jo uporablja, "
"lahko podokno <guilabel>Kontekst</guilabel> zagotovi zelo bogato vsebino, "
"kot so AJAX, video in animacije, vse na privlačen način. Več o <link linkend="
"\"the-context-pane\">kontekstnem podoknu</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6585
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To accompany the <guilabel>Context</guilabel> pane, we developed a new, "
"space efficient playlist. In order to preserve horizontal space, it groups "
"the track name, artist, album name and cover art together, and allows "
"further grouping by album names. Plus you can rearrange it to your heart's "
"content! If you prefer the old 1.4 playlist, you can have that too. See "
"<link linkend=\"changing-the-playlist-layout\">Changing the Playlist layout</"
"link> for more."
msgstr ""
"Za spremljavo podokna <guilabel>Kontekst</guilabel> smo razvili nov, "
"prostorsko učinkovit seznam predvajanja. Da bi ohranil vodoravni prostor, "
"združuje ime skladbe, izvajalca, ime albuma in naslovnico ter omogoča "
"nadaljnje združevanje po imenih albumov. Poleg tega ga lahko preuredite po "
"želji! Če imate raje stari seznam predvajanja 1.4, lahko imate tudi tega. Za "
"več glejte <link linkend=\"changing-the-playlist-layout\">Spreminjanje "
"postavitve seznama predvajanja</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6586
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Another great gem is the video support. Watching your music videos inside "
"&amarok; feels great!"
msgstr ""
"Še en velik biser je podpora za video. Gledanje glasbenih videoposnetkov "
"znotraj &amarok; počuti se odlično!"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6587
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We can't forget the <guilabel>Dynamic Playlists</guilabel>, which extend the "
"old <guilabel>Dynamic Playlists</guilabel>. They allow you to define an "
"automatically populated playlist, based on specific probability driven "
"criteria called <quote>biases</quote>. The <guilabel>Dynamic Playlists</"
"guilabel> is joined by the new <guilabel>Automatic Playlist Generator</"
"guilabel>, used to generate lists for specific purposes and of a specified "
"length. See <link linkend=\"dynamic-playlists\">Dynamic Playlists</link> and "
"<link linkend=\"automatic-playlist-generator\">Automatic Playlist Generator</"
"link> for more information."
msgstr ""
"Ne smemo pozabiti na <guilabel>Dinamične sezname predvajanja</guilabel>, ki "
"razširjajo stare <guilabel>Dinamične sezname predvajanja</guilabel>. "
"Omogočajo vam definiranje samodejno izpolnjenega seznama predvajanja, ki "
"temelji na določenih verjetnostnih kriterijih, imenovanih "
"<quote>pristranskosti</quote>. <guilabel>Dinamičnim seznamom predvajanja</"
"guilabel> se pridružuje novi <guilabel>Samodejni generator seznamov "
"predvajanja</guilabel>, ki se uporablja za ustvarjanje seznamov za posebne "
"namene in določene dolžine. Za več informacij glejte <link linkend=\"dynamic-"
"playlists\">Dinamični seznami predvajanja</link> in <link linkend="
"\"automatic-playlist-generator\">Samodejni generator seznamov predvajanja</"
"link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6589
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are many more great features like advanced scripting, dynamic "
"collections, usability improvements, improved media devices handling, a new "
"podcast manager, support for more software platforms, and others."
msgstr ""
"Obstaja veliko več odličnih funkcij, kot so napredno skriptiranje, dinamične "
"zbirke, izboljšave uporabnosti, izboljšano upravljanje medijskih naprav, nov "
"upravljalnik podcastov, podpora za več programskih platform in druge."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6593
#, no-c-format
msgid "Can I use Amarok without KDE?"
msgstr "Ali lahko uporabljam Amarok brez KDE?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6594
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&amarok; requires parts of KDE to be installed to run, but will run fine in "
"Gnome or other desktop environments, including Windows and OS X. For "
"&amarok; to run, kdelibs and kdebase-runtime need to be installed."
msgstr ""
"&amarok; za delovanje zahteva namestitev delov KDE, vendar bo dobro deloval "
"v Gnome ali drugih namiznih okoljih, vključno z Windows in OS X. Za &amarok; "
"za delovanje je treba namestiti kdelibs in kdebase-runtime."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6596
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For some features to work correctly, such as the on-screen display, your "
"window manager must be configured to support the relevant "
"<emphasis>freedesktop.org</emphasis> standards. More about running &amarok; "
"on other platforms <link linkend=\"amarok-on-other-platforms\">here</link>."
msgstr ""
"Za pravilno delovanje nekaterih funkcij, kot je prikaz na zaslonu, mora biti "
"vaš upravljalnik oken konfiguriran tako, da podpira ustrezne standarde "
"<emphasis>freedesktop.org</emphasis>. Več o izvajanju &amarok; na drugih "
"platformah <link linkend=\"amarok-on-other-platforms\">tukaj</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6599
#, no-c-format
msgid "Why does Amarok use KDElibs?"
msgstr "Zakaj Amarok uporablja KDElibs?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6600
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We are committed to supporting &amarok; on all platforms. We use KDElibs and "
"Qt because they provide an excellent development environment. Aside from "
"&Linux; and BSD, &amarok; works on Windows and MacOS, and there are "
"installers available, but unfortunately we don't have (yet) the resources to "
"offer full support for those operating systems. Almost all of our developers "
"use free operating systems, and those have priority for us. We do however "
"welcome Windows and OS X developers willing to help, and improve &amarok; on "
"those platforms."
msgstr ""
"Zavezani smo podpori &amarok; na vseh platformah. Uporabljamo KDElibs in Qt, "
"ker nudita odlično razvojno okolje. Poleg &Linux; in BSD, &amarok; deluje v "
"sistemih Windows in MacOS, na voljo pa so tudi namestitveni programi, vendar "
"žal (še) nimamo virov, da bi ponudili popolno podporo za te operacijske "
"sisteme. Skoraj vsi naši razvijalci uporabljajo brezplačne operacijske "
"sisteme in ti imajo za nas prednost. Vendar pozdravljamo razvijalce za "
"Windows in OS X, ki so pripravljeni pomagati in izboljšati &amarok; na teh "
"platformah."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6604
#, no-c-format
msgid "General usage"
msgstr "Splošna uporaba"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6605
#, no-c-format
msgid "How can I control Amarok from the keyboard?"
msgstr "Kako lahko upravljam Amarok s tipkovnice?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6606
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Keyboard shortcuts are available; see our <link linkend=\"keybinding-"
"reference\">Keybinding Reference page</link> for more information."
msgstr ""
"Na voljo so bližnjice na tipkovnici; za več informacij si oglejte našo <link "
"linkend=\"keybinding-reference\">stran z referenčnimi navodili za vezavo "
"tipk</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6608
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To control &amarok; from the console, type <userinput>amarok --help-all</"
"userinput> for a current complete list of available control commands."
msgstr ""
"Za nadzor &amarok; s konzole vnesite <userinput>amarok --help-all</"
"userinput> za trenutni celoten seznam razpoložljivih nadzornih ukazov."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6611
#, no-c-format
msgid "Where can I get support for Amarok?"
msgstr "Kje lahko dobim podporo za Amarok?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6612
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are several options. Often times problems you have with the initial "
"install of &amarok; are best answered by experts of your particular &UNIX; "
"or &Linux; distribution. You may seek help from fellow users and developers "
"at the <ulink url=\"https://discuss.kde.org/tag/amarok\">Discuss server "
"under the Amarok category</ulink> and the <ulink url=\"irc://irc.libera.chat/"
"amarok\">Amarok IRC channel</ulink> at irc.libera.chat channel #amarok."
msgstr ""
"Možnosti je več. Pogosto imate težave z začetno namestitvijo &amarok; "
"najbolje odgovorijo strokovnjaki za vaš &UNIX; ali &Linux; distribucija. "
"Pomoč lahko poiščete pri drugih uporabnikih in razvijalcih na forumu <ulink "
"url=\"https://discuss.kde.org/tag/amarok\">pod kategorijo Amarok</ulink> in "
"<ulink url=\"irc://irc.libera.chat/amarok\">Kanal IRC Amarok</ulink> na "
"kanalu irc.libera.chat #amarok."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6614
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that <ulink url=\"http://bugs.kde.org\">bugzilla</ulink> is not a place "
"to seek support. Please do enter a bug if you are serious about helping fix "
"a bug in &amarok; itself."
msgstr ""
"Upoštevajte, da <ulink url=\"http://bugs.kde.org\">bugzilla</ulink> ni kraj "
"za iskanje podpore. Prosimo, vnesite napako, če resno nameravate pomagati "
"odpraviti napako v &amarok; sama."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6617
#, no-c-format
msgid "How do I report a bug?"
msgstr "Kako prijavim napako?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6618
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you find a bug in &amarok;, please submit it to the <ulink url=\"https://"
"bugs.kde.org\">KDE bugzilla instance</ulink>. To make a complete bug report, "
"please always include the following information:"
msgstr ""
"Če v &amarok;u najdete napako, jo pošljite <ulink url=\"https://bugs.kde.org"
"\">primerku KDE bugzilla</ulink>. Če želite pripraviti popolno poročilo o "
"napakah, vedno vključite naslednje informacije:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6621
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The exact &amarok; version (the version can be found in "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Help</guimenu><guimenuitem>About Amarok</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>). You should not report bugs for &amarok; versions older than "
"the current stable release as we do not provide backport fixes."
msgstr ""
"Natančen &amarok; različico (različico lahko najdete v "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Pomoči</guimenu><guimenuitem>O Amaroku</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>). Ne smete poročati o napakah za &amarok; različice, ki so "
"starejše od trenutne stabilne izdaje, saj ne nudimo popravkov za povratna "
"vrata."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6622
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The exact KDE and Qt version, even if you do not run &amarok; in KDE "
"(<menuchoice><guimenu>Help</guimenu><guimenuitem>About KDE</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>)"
msgstr ""
"Natančna različica KDE in Qt, tudi če ne zaženete &amarok; v KDE "
"(<menuchoice><guimenu>Pomoč</guimenu><guimenuitem>O KDE</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6623
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The exact Phonon backend. You can find this information in the Diagnostics "
"(<menuchoice><guimenu>Help</guimenu><guimenuitem>Diagnostics</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>)"
msgstr ""
"Točno zaledje Phonon. Te informacije najdete v Diagnostiki "
"(<menuchoice><guimenu>Pomoč</guimenu><guimenuitem>Diagnostika</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6624
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whether the bug is reproducible. Please do not report bugs that you can not "
"reproduce as these are almost impossible to fix."
msgstr ""
"Ali je hrošč ponovljiv. Prosimo, da ne poročate o napakah, ki jih ne morete "
"reproducirati, saj jih je skoraj nemogoče popraviti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6625
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exact steps how to reproduce the bug"
msgstr "Natančni koraki, kako reproducirati napako"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6627
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If any of these information is missing the bug report is not complete. "
"Please also be prepared to answer questions from the developers or bug "
"triagers and eventually test other settings."
msgstr ""
"Če katera od teh informacij manjka, poročilo o napaki ni popolno. Bodite "
"pripravljeni tudi odgovoriti na vprašanja razvijalcev ali triagerjev hroščev "
"in na koncu preizkusiti druge nastavitve."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6631
#, no-c-format
msgid "Questions about the Playlist"
msgstr "Vprašanja o seznamu predvajanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6632
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"More about the <link linkend=\"the-playlist-pane\">Playlist here</link>."
msgstr ""
"Več o <link linkend=\"the-playlist-pane\">seznamu predvajanja tukaj</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6634
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When I start Amarok, I see an empty playlist. How do I actually get tracks "
"in there?"
msgstr ""
"Ko zaženem Amarok, vidim prazen seznam predvajanja. Kako naj dejansko dobim "
"skladbe tja?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6635
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the <guilabel>Media Sources</guilabel> on the left side to navigate to "
"the desired artist/album/track. Then drag the files into the "
"<guilabel>Playlist</guilabel> part on the right. You can use "
"<guilabel>Dynamic Playlists</guilabel> or the <guilabel>Automatic Playlist "
"Generator</guilabel> to populate your playlist. You can also drag files in "
"from any file manager, such as &dolphin;. You may also double-click a track, "
"artist or genre in your <guilabel>Media Sources</guilabel> or file-system, "
"or right-click and <guilabel>Add to Playlist</guilabel> or <guilabel>Replace "
"Playlist</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite <guilabel>Medijski viri</guilabel> na levi strani, da se pomaknete "
"do želenega izvajalca/albuma/skladbe. Nato povlecite datoteke v del "
"<guilabel>Playlist</guilabel> na desni. Za zapolnitev seznama predvajanja "
"lahko uporabite <guilabel>Dinamične sezname predvajanja</guilabel> ali "
"<guilabel>Samodejni generator seznamov predvajanja</guilabel>. Datoteke "
"lahko povlečete tudi iz katerega koli upravljalnika datotek, kot je "
"&dolphin;. Prav tako lahko dvokliknete skladbo, izvajalca ali zvrst v "
"<guilabel>medijskih virih</guilabel> ali datotečnem sistemu, ali z desno "
"miškino tipko kliknete in <guilabel>Dodaj na seznam predvajanja</guilabel> "
"ali <guilabel>Zamenjaj seznam predvajanja</guilabel>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6638
#, no-c-format
msgid "How do I remove tracks from the Playlist?"
msgstr "Kako odstranim skladbe s seznama predvajanja?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6639
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select the track(s) you want to remove, and press the <keycap>Delete</"
"keycap> key. Or right-click the selection and choose <guilabel>Remove From "
"Playlist</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Izberite skladbo(e), ki jo želite odstraniti, in pritisnite tipko "
"<keycap>Delete</keycap>. Ali pa z desno miškino tipko kliknite izbor in "
"izberite <guilabel>Odstrani s seznama predvajanja</guilabel>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6642
#, no-c-format
msgid "How can I load a playlist?"
msgstr "Kako lahko naložim seznam predvajanja?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6643
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Just drag and drop the playlist file into the <guilabel>Playlist</guilabel>, "
"like you would do with any other file. It's that simple!"
msgstr ""
"Preprosto povlecite in spustite datoteko seznama predvajanja v "
"<guilabel>Seznam predvajanja</guilabel>, kot bi storili z vsako drugo "
"datoteko. Tako preprosto je!"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6646
#, no-c-format
msgid "How can I save the current playlist?"
msgstr "Kako lahko shranim trenutni seznam predvajanja?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6647
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click the <inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"Icon-"
"document-save.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> "
"button in the <guilabel>Playlist</guilabel> toolbar. Slow-click the disc "
"icon to chose to save to your harddisk, or to the database."
msgstr ""
"Kliknite gumb <inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"Icon-"
"document-save.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> v "
"orodni vrstici <guilabel>Seznam predvajanja</guilabel>. Počasi kliknite "
"ikono diska, da izberete shranjevanje na trdi disk ali v bazo podatkov."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6651
#, no-c-format
msgid "Playback Questions"
msgstr "Vprašanja glede predvajanja"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6652
#, no-c-format
msgid "How do I play audio CDs?"
msgstr "Kako predvajam zvočne CD-je?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6653
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Audio CDs are treated differently than data CDs, which are also supported. "
"When you insert an audio CD, it will be shown as a local collection. Drag to "
"the playlist or <emphasis>Pop-Up Dropper</emphasis>, or right-click the "
"selected tracks and choose <guilabel>Add to Playlist</guilabel> or "
"<guilabel>Replace Playlist</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Zvočni CD-ji se obravnavajo drugače kot podatkovni CD-ji, ki so prav tako "
"podprti. Ko vstavite zvočni CD, bo prikazan kot lokalna zbirka. Povlecite na "
"seznam predvajanja ali <emphasis>Pojavno kapalko</emphasis> ali z desno "
"miškino tipko kliknite izbrane skladbe in izberite <guilabel>Dodaj na seznam "
"predvajanja</guilabel> ali <guilabel>Zamenjaj seznam predvajanja</guilabel>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6656
#, no-c-format
msgid "What media types does Amarok support?"
msgstr "Katere medijske vrste podpira Amarok?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6657
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&amarok; does not play music by itself, but lets Phonon do that job, "
"specifically the VLC or GStreamer backends of Phonon. Therefore, whatever "
"files they can play, &amarok; can play. To analyse file tags, &amarok; uses "
"Taglib, which supports most file types that contain metadata."
msgstr ""
"&amarok; sam ne predvaja glasbe, ampak to delo prepusti Phononu, še posebej "
"zaledju Phonona VLC ali GStreamer. Torej, ne glede na datoteke, ki jih lahko "
"predvajajo, &amarok; lahko igra. Za analizo oznak datoteke &amarok; "
"uporablja Taglib, ki podpira večino vrst datotek, ki vsebujejo metapodatke."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6660
#, no-c-format
msgid "What is Phonon? What are Phonon backends?"
msgstr "Kaj je Phonon? Kaj so ozadja Phonon?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6661
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Phonon</emphasis> is the multimedia framework of KDE 4. You can "
"find more information <link linkend=\"playback\">here</link>."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Phonon</emphasis> je multimedijsko ogrodje KDE 4. Več informacij "
"najdete <link linkend=\"playback\">tukaj</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6663
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We currently recommend both the Gstreamer and VLC backend as both are "
"actively maintained. If you want to play streams you should use the VLC "
"backend only as the Gstreamer backend has some shortcomings in this regard. "
"Make sure you do not use any other backend as those are obsolete."
msgstr ""
"Trenutno priporočamo zaledje Gstreamer in VLC, saj se oba aktivno "
"vzdržujeta. Če želite predvajati tokove, uporabite samo zaledje VLC, saj ima "
"zaledje Gstreamer v zvezi s tem nekaj pomanjkljivosti. Prepričajte se, da ne "
"uporabljate nobenega drugega zaledja, ker je zastarelo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6665
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are using the Phonon-backend-gstreamer make sure you only use plugins "
"from one single gstreamer version, else your sound will be compromised."
msgstr ""
"Če uporabljate Phonon-backend-gstreamer, se prepričajte, da uporabljate samo "
"vtičnike iz ene same različice gstreamerja, sicer bo vaš zvok ogrožen."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6668
#, no-c-format
msgid "Amarok won't play mp3s, what can I do?"
msgstr "Amarok noče predvajati mp3, kaj naj storim?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6669
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You probably lack the codecs required by your particular Phonon backend "
"(Gstreamer, or VLC). Please report this to your distribution if you were not "
"prompted to install them automatically when you started &amarok; for the "
"first time."
msgstr ""
"Verjetno vam primanjkuje kodekov, ki jih zahteva vaš določen Phonon backend "
"(Gstreamer ali VLC). Prijavite to svoji distribuciji, če niste bili pozvani, "
"da jih samodejno namestite, ko ste zagnali &amarok; prvič."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6672
#, no-c-format
msgid "I have the codecs, but Amarok still won't play mp4s and mkas"
msgstr "Imam kodeke, vendar Amarok še vedno ne predvaja mp4 in mka"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6673
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using some phonon backend, like the gstreamer one, &amarok; might "
"refuse to play <filename>mp4</filename> and <filename>mka</filename> files. "
"This is a known problem, see <emphasis role=\"strikethrough\"><ulink url="
"\"https://bugs.kde.org/show_bug.cgi?id=290168\">bug #290168</ulink></"
"emphasis> for more technical information."
msgstr ""
"Pri uporabi nekega fononskega zaledja, kot je gstreamer, &amarok; lahko "
"zavrne predvajanje datotek <filename>mp4</filename> in <filename>mka</"
"filename>. To je znana težava, glejte <emphasis role=\"strikethrough"
"\"><ulink url=\"https://bugs.kde.org/show_bug.cgi?id=290168\">napaka "
"#290168</ulink></emphasis> za več tehničnih informacij."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6675
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A very simple workaround is to change the file extension. Change "
"<filename>mp4</filename> extension to <filename>m4a</filename> and for "
"<filename>mka</filename> change it to <filename>mkv</filename>. Of course "
"you must be sure the files contains audio only. You can use the ffprobe "
"command to look at what data streams are present in the file. If the file "
"has a video stream it must be stripped out. There are a lot of tools able to "
"edit these formats and most of them are based on <filename>ffmpeg</filename>/"
"<filename>libav</filename>, which you can use if you are familiar with them. "
"If you prefer graphical tools one possible choice is <ulink url=\"http://www."
"avidemux.org/\">avidemux</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Zelo preprosta rešitev je sprememba pripone datoteke. Spremenite pripono "
"<filename>mp4</filename> v <filename>m4a</filename> in za <filename>mka</"
"filename> jo spremenite v <filename>mkv</filename>. Seveda morate biti "
"prepričani, da datoteke vsebujejo samo zvok. Z ukazom ffprobe lahko "
"pogledate, kateri podatkovni tokovi so prisotni v datoteki. Če ima datoteka "
"video tok, ga je treba odstraniti. Obstaja veliko orodij za urejanje teh "
"formatov in večina jih temelji na <filename>ffmpeg</filename>/"
"<filename>libav</filename>, ki jih lahko uporabite, če jih poznate. Če imate "
"raje grafična orodja, je ena možna izbira <ulink url=\"http://www.avidemux."
"org/\">avidemux</ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6677
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is a quick example how you can remove a video stream from an "
"<filename>mp4</filename> video with ffmpeg. Stripping a video stream from an "
"<filename>mkv</filename> file is the same. First check if there is a video "
"stream"
msgstr ""
"To je hiter primer, kako lahko odstranite video tok iz videoposnetka "
"<filename>mp4</filename> s ffmpeg. Odstranjevanje video toka iz datoteke "
"<filename>mkv</filename> je enako. Najprej preverite, ali obstaja video tok"

#. Tag: command
#: index.docbook:6679
#, no-c-format
msgid "$ ffprobe example.mp4 2&gt;&amp;1 | grep Video"
msgstr "$ ffprobe example.mp4 2&gt;&amp;1 | grep Video"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:6681
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>Stream #0.1(und): Video: h264 (Baseline), yuv420p, 480x360 [PAR 1:1 "
"DAR 4:3], 242 kb/s, 25 fps, 25 tbr, 25k tbn, 50k tbc</command>"
msgstr ""
"<command>Tok #0.1(und): Video: h264 (osnovna linija), yuv420p, 480x360 [PAR "
"1:1 DAR 4:3], 242 kb/s, 25 fps, 25 tbr, 25k tbn, 50k tbc</command >"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6683
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the output of the previous command is null there is no video stream in "
"the file. To create an <filename>m4a</filename> file with just the audio "
"stream you can use something like"
msgstr ""
"Če je rezultat prejšnjega ukaza nič, v datoteki ni video toka. Če želite "
"ustvariti datoteko <filename>m4a</filename> samo z zvočnim tokom, lahko "
"uporabite nekaj takega"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:6685
#, no-c-format
msgid "ffmpeg -i example.mp4 -acodec copy -vn example.m4a"
msgstr "ffmpeg -i primer.mp4 -akodec kopija -vn primer.m4a"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6687
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also use <filename>avconv</filename> in place of <filename>ffmpeg</"
"filename> with the same options, where"
msgstr ""
"Uporabite lahko tudi <filename>avconv</filename> namesto <filename>ffmpeg</"
"filename> z enakimi možnostmi, kjer"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6690
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>-i example.mp4</emphasis> option is the input file name"
msgstr "Možnost <emphasis>-i example.mp4</emphasis> je ime vhodne datoteke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6691
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>-acodec copy</emphasis> is used to not encode again the audio "
"stream but just copy it. This to avoid quality loss, but you can also encode "
"in a different format if you want, and you are not forced to use m4a "
"container in this case"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>-acodec copy</emphasis> se uporablja, da se zvočni tok ne kodira "
"znova, ampak samo kopira. To se izogne izgubi kakovosti, lahko pa tudi "
"kodirate v drugi obliki, če želite, in v tem primeru vam ni treba uporabiti "
"vsebnika m4a"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6692
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>-vn</emphasis> strips the video stream"
msgstr "<emphasis>-vn</emphasis> odstrani video tok"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6693
#, no-c-format
msgid "<replaceable>example.m4a</replaceable> is the output file name"
msgstr "<replaceable>example.m4a</replaceable> je ime izhodne datoteke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6695
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Another possible workaround is to change the phonon backend. For example the "
"VLC backend doesn't suffer this problem."
msgstr ""
"Druga možna rešitev je sprememba fononskega ozadja. Zaledje VLC na primer "
"nima te težave."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6698
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"I have a second soundcard and I'm using ALSA. How do I make Amarok use it "
"instead of the default?"
msgstr ""
"Imam drugo zvočno kartico in uporabljam ALSA. Kako naj ga Amarok uporabi "
"namesto privzetega?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6699
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configure this in the Phonon system settings module. "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guisubmenu>Configure Amarok</"
"guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Playback</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Configure Phonon</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>"
msgstr ""
"Konfigurirajte to v modulu sistemskih nastavitev Phonon. "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu><guisubmenu>Konfiguriraj Amarok</"
"guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Predvajanje</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Konfiguriraj "
"Phonon</guimenuitem></menuchoice>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6702
#, no-c-format
msgid "Where's the equalizer?"
msgstr "Kje je izenačevalnik?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6703
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The equalizer is only available if you are using the phonon-backend-"
"gstreamer. You can find the equalizer in the <guilabel>Tools</guilabel> menu."
msgstr ""
"Izenačevalnik je na voljo le, če uporabljate phonon-backend-gstreamer. "
"Izenačevalnik najdete v meniju <guilabel>Orodja</guilabel>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6706
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"How can I control the volume in Amarok only without having to change in KMix?"
msgstr ""
"Kako lahko nadzorujem glasnost samo v Amaroku, ne da bi moral spremeniti v "
"KMixu?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6707
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most distributions ship the <guilabel>PulseAudio</guilabel> sound-daemon "
"nowadays which handles the sound settings system-wide. If you can't change "
"the volume in &amarok; independently of &kmix;, then your "
"<application>PulseAudio</application> settings have the option"
msgstr ""
"Večina distribucij danes pošilja zvočni demon <guilabel>PulseAudio</"
"guilabel>, ki obravnava nastavitve zvoka v celotnem sistemu. Če ne morete "
"spremeniti glasnosti v &amarok; neodvisno od &kmix;, potem imajo vaše "
"nastavitve <application>PulseAudio</application> možnost"

#. Tag: userinput
#: index.docbook:6709
#, no-c-format
msgid "flat-volume=yes"
msgstr "flat-volume=da"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6711
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"enabled. Depending on your distribution this is located either in the file "
"<filename>$HOME/.pulse/daemon.conf</filename> or in the system file "
"<filename>/etc/pulse/daemon.conf</filename>. More information about "
"Pulseudio-specific settings can be found in <ulink url=\"http://linux.die."
"net/man/5/pulse-daemon.conf\">pulse-daemon.conf man page</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"omogočeno. Odvisno od vaše distribucije se to nahaja v datoteki <filename>"
"$HOME/.pulse/daemon.conf</filename> ali v sistemski datoteki <filename>/etc/"
"pulse/daemon.conf</filename>. Več informacij o nastavitvah, specifičnih za "
"Pulseudio, najdete na <ulink url=\"http://linux.die.net/man/5/pulse-daemon."
"conf\">strani priročnika za pulse-daemon.conf</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6714
#, no-c-format
msgid "How do I turn on visualizations?"
msgstr "Kako vklopim vizualizacije?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6715
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Visualizations come in the form of an applet. For more information please "
"see the <link linkend=\"applets\">applets page</link>. Visualizations are "
"currently under development and may be buggy at this time."
msgstr ""
"Vizualizacije so na voljo v obliki programčka. Za več informacij obiščite "
"<link linkend=\"applets\">stran z programčki</link>. Vizualizacije so "
"trenutno v razvoju in so trenutno morda hrošče."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6718
#, no-c-format
msgid "How can I add podcasts?"
msgstr "Kako lahko dodam poddaje?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6719
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Go to <guilabel>Podcast</guilabel> section in the <guilabel>Media Sources</"
"guilabel> pane and then select <guilabel>Add Podcast...</guilabel> Add the "
"podcast URL where indicated. More about podcasts <link linkend=\"podcasts"
"\">here</link>."
msgstr ""
"Pojdite na razdelek <guilabel>Podcast</guilabel> v podoknu "
"<guilabel>Medijski viri</guilabel> in nato izberite <guilabel>Dodaj "
"podcast ...</guilabel> Dodajte URL podcasta, kjer je označeno. Več o "
"podcastih <link linkend=\"podcasts\">tukaj</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6721
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We also have some services, such as gpodder and Podcast Directory to help "
"you find great podcasts. Enable services in the <guilabel>Settings</"
"guilabel> menu: <menuchoice><guimenu>Configure Amarok</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Plugins</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"Imamo tudi nekaj storitev, kot sta gpodder in Podcast Directory, ki vam "
"pomagajo najti odlične poddaje. Omogočite storitve v meniju "
"<guilabel>Nastavitve</guilabel>: <menuchoice><guimenu>Konfiguriraj Amarok</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Vtičniki</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6724
#, no-c-format
msgid "How can I use Amarok to stream to my own radio station?"
msgstr "Kako lahko uporabim Amarok za pretakanje na lastno radijsko postajo?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6725
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to stream directly to an icecast or shoutcast server the answer "
"simply is: it is not supported. You could use <ulink url=\"http://giss.tv/"
"sahabuntu/doc/idjc.html\">IDJC</ulink> for that."
msgstr ""
"Če želite pretakati neposredno na strežnik icecast ali shoutcast, je odgovor "
"preprost: ni podprt. Za to lahko uporabite <ulink url=\"http://giss.tv/"
"sahabuntu/doc/idjc.html\">IDJC</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6729
#, no-c-format
msgid "Collection questions"
msgstr "Zbirka vprašanj"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6730
#, no-c-format
msgid "Folder not properly picked up"
msgstr "Mapa ni pravilno pobrana"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6731
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you find that most of your music is recognized by &amarok;, but some "
"folders are not properly picked up, open a console and type"
msgstr ""
"Če ugotovite, da &amarok; prepozna večino vaše glasbe, vendar nekatere mape "
"niso pravilno izbrane, odprite konzolo in vnesite"

#. Tag: userinput
#: index.docbook:6733
#, no-c-format
msgid "touch <replaceable>folder</replaceable>"
msgstr "dotaknite se <replaceable>mape</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6735
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"where <replaceable>folder</replaceable> is the path to the folder that has "
"the problem. Then select <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Configure Amarok</guimenuitem></menuchoice> in &amarok; "
"main window menu, open <guilabel>Collection</guilabel> page and click the "
"<guilabel>Full Rescan</guilabel> button. Your folder should be visible again "
"now."
msgstr ""
"kjer je <replaceable>mapa</replaceable> pot do mape, v kateri je težava. "
"Nato izberite <menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Konfiguriraj Amarok</guimenuitem></menuchoice> v "
"&amarok; v meniju glavnega okna odprite stran <guilabel>Zbirka</guilabel> in "
"kliknite gumb <guilabel>Popolno ponovno skeniranje</guilabel>. Vaša mapa bi "
"morala biti zdaj spet vidna."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6737
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"this will not work on Windows, as the touch command is specific to &Linux; "
"and BSD-like systems."
msgstr ""
"to ne bo delovalo v operacijskem sistemu Windows, ker je ukaz dotik "
"specifičen za &Linux; in BSD podobnih sistemov."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6740
#, no-c-format
msgid "Can I use removable media inside Amarok?"
msgstr "Ali lahko v Amaroku uporabljam izmenljive medije?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6741
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&amarok; has a greatly improved support for the media devices based on "
"Solid, the KDE hardware layer, that doesn't need a lot of configuration. You "
"should be able to just plug in your device and access it within &amarok;. "
"Also, thanks to the <emphasis>Dynamic Collections</emphasis>, your media "
"devices could become part of your music collection, and be searchable and "
"accessible within the <guilabel>Local Music</guilabel> section of the "
"<guilabel>Media Sources</guilabel> pane when it's connected."
msgstr ""
"&amarok; ima močno izboljšano podporo za medijske naprave, ki temeljijo na "
"Solidu, sloju strojne opreme KDE, ki ne potrebuje veliko konfiguracije. "
"Morali bi imeti možnost samo priključiti svojo napravo in dostopati do nje "
"znotraj &amarok;. Prav tako lahko zahvaljujoč <emphasis>Dynamic Collections</"
"emphasis> vaše predstavnostne naprave postanejo del vaše glasbene zbirke ter "
"jih je mogoče iskati in dostopati v razdelku <guilabel>Lokalna glasba</"
"guilabel> v <guilabel>Virih medijev </guilabel> podoknu, ko je povezan."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6743
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can transfer your songs, albums and artists from your local collection "
"by right-clicking, selecting <guilabel>Copy to Collection</guilabel> and "
"picking your device; and you can also do it in the other way: right-click "
"and select <menuchoice><guimenu>Copy to Collection</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Local Collection</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. More about "
"&amarok; and devices <link linkend=\"working-with-media-devices\">here</"
"link>."
msgstr ""
"Svoje pesmi, albume in izvajalce lahko prenesete iz svoje lokalne zbirke "
"tako, da z desno miškino tipko kliknete, izberete <guilabel>Kopiraj v "
"zbirko</guilabel> in izberete svojo napravo; lahko pa tudi drugače: z desno "
"miškino tipko kliknite in izberite <menuchoice><guimenu>Kopiraj v zbirko</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Lokalna zbirka</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Več o "
"&amarok; in naprave <link linkend=\"working-with-media-devices\">tukaj</"
"link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6746
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Can I use the old Amarok's collection in Amarok 2? Will my tags, score are "
"ratings be lost?"
msgstr ""
"Ali lahko uporabim staro Amarokovo zbirko v Amaroku 2? Ali bodo moje oznake, "
"ocene ali ocene izgubljene?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6747
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A database importer is available. You will be able to keep your ratings and "
"statistics just fine. More <link linkend=\"collection\">here</link>."
msgstr ""
"Na voljo je uvoznik baze podatkov. Svoje ocene in statistiko boste lahko "
"dobro obdržali. Več <link linkend=\"collection\">tukaj</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6751
#, no-c-format
msgid "General questions"
msgstr "Splošna vprašanja"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6752
#, no-c-format
msgid "What are scripts?"
msgstr "Kaj so skripte?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6753
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"They are little pieces of software that add some functions to &amarok;. "
"There are a lot of scripts, and you can find them in <ulink url=\"http://www."
"kde-apps.org/index.php?xcontentmode=57\">kde-apps.org</ulink> or you can "
"find and install them inside &amarok; using the <guilabel>Script Manager</"
"guilabel>. More details can be found <link linkend=\"script-manager\">here</"
"link>. You will find the <guilabel>Script Manager</guilabel> from the "
"<guilabel>Settings</guilabel> menu, <menuchoice><guimenu>Configure Amarok</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Scripts</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"So majhni kosi programske opreme, ki &amarok;u dodajo nekaj funkcij. Obstaja "
"veliko skriptov in najdete jih na <ulink url=\"http://www.kde-apps.org/index."
"php?xcontentmode=57\">kde-apps.org</ulink> ali jih lahko najde in namesti "
"znotraj &amarok; z uporabo <guilabel>Upravljalnika skriptov</guilabel>. Več "
"podrobnosti najdete <link linkend=\"script-manager\">tukaj</link>. "
"<guilabel>Upravljalnik skriptov</guilabel> boste našli v meniju "
"<guilabel>Nastavitve</guilabel>, <menuchoice><guimenu>Konfiguriraj Amarok</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Skripte</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6756
#, no-c-format
msgid "Can I use Amarok 1.4 scripts in Amarok 2?"
msgstr "Ali lahko uporabljam skripte Amarok 1.4 v Amaroku 2?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6757
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"No. A new and powerful scripting API has been created, which provides huge "
"improvements but won't let you use your old scripts. The new scripting "
"system is based on QtScript and will significantly reduce &amarok;'s "
"dependencies, a huge problem for non-technical and cross-platform users, and "
"will greatly reduce the amount of external processes launched at runtime. "
"Another advantage is that the new API will allow much deeper integration "
"with &amarok; than the old scripting system. <ulink url=\"http://community."
"kde.org/Amarok/Development/Script_API\">Amarok Scripting API</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Ne. Ustvarjen je bil nov in zmogljiv API za skripte, ki zagotavlja velike "
"izboljšave, vendar vam ne dovoljuje uporabe starih skriptov. Novi skriptni "
"sistem temelji na QtScriptu in bo znatno zmanjšal odvisnosti &amarok;a, kar "
"je velika težava za netehnične uporabnike in uporabnike, ki uporabljajo več "
"platform, in bo močno zmanjšal količino zunanjih procesov, ki se zaženejo "
"med izvajanjem. Druga prednost je, da bo novi API omogočil veliko globljo "
"integracijo z &amarok; kot stari skriptni sistem. <ulink url=\"http://"
"community.kde.org/Amarok/Development/Script_API\">API za skriptiranje "
"Amarok</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6760
#, no-c-format
msgid "What are Moodbars?"
msgstr "Kaj so vrstice razpoloženja?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6761
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Moodbars</guilabel> show the mood of a song in the progress bar. "
"More about <guilabel>Moodbar</guilabel> <link linkend=\"the-moodbar\">here</"
"link>."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Vrstice razpoloženja</guilabel> prikazujejo razpoloženje pesmi v "
"vrstici napredka. Več o <guilabel>Moodbar</guilabel> <link linkend=\"the-"
"moodbar\">tukaj</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6764
#, no-c-format
msgid "Can I play video files?"
msgstr "Ali lahko predvajam video datoteke?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6765
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&amarok; is mainly a music player so no video file management, collection "
"support, DVD playback, subtitles, or any other sophisticated features are "
"available."
msgstr ""
"&amarok; je v glavnem predvajalnik glasbe, zato ni na voljo upravljanje "
"video datotek, podpora za zbiranje, predvajanje DVD-jev, podnapisi ali druge "
"prefinjene funkcije."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6768
#, no-c-format
msgid "Is it Amarok, AmaroK or amaroK?"
msgstr "Je Amarok, AmaroK ali amaroK?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6769
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is &amarok;! The former spelling was <emphasis>amaroK</emphasis>, but it "
"was changed due to its strange look around 2005."
msgstr ""
"To je &amarok;! Prejšnje črkovanje je bilo <emphasis>amaroK</emphasis>, "
"vendar je bilo okoli leta 2005 spremenjeno zaradi čudnega videza."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6772
#, no-c-format
msgid "How are track scores determined?"
msgstr "Kako se določijo rezultati proge?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6773
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&amarok; assigns a score (a number 0-100) to a song based on how many times "
"you've listened to it and whether you skip the song without it finishing. "
"Every time the song finishes playing, the score is changed."
msgstr ""
"&amarok; dodeli oceno (število 0-100) pesmi glede na to, kolikokrat ste jo "
"poslušali in ali ste pesem preskočili, ne da bi jo dokončali. Vsakič, ko se "
"pesem konča, se rezultat spremeni."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6775
#, no-c-format
msgid "Here you have an example script that can calculate scores:"
msgstr "Tukaj imate primer skripta, ki lahko izračuna rezultate:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:6777
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"if( playcount &lt;= 0 ) # not supposed to be less, but what the hell.\n"
"       newscore = ( prevscore + percentage ) / 2\n"
"   else\n"
"       newscore = ( ( prevscore * playcount ) + percentage ) / ( playcount + "
"1 )\n"
"   end"
msgstr ""
"if( playcount &lt;= 0 ) # not supposed to be less, but what the hell.\n"
"       newscore = ( prevscore + percentage ) / 2\n"
"   else\n"
"       newscore = ( ( prevscore * playcount ) + percentage ) / ( playcount + "
"1 )\n"
"   end"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6779
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can easily create your own script with your own algorithm. Look at the "
"<ulink url=\"http://community.kde.org/Amarok/Development/"
"Scripting_HowTo_2.0\">Script-Writing-Howto</ulink> for further information."
msgstr ""
"Enostavno lahko ustvarite svoj skript z lastnim algoritmom. Za dodatne "
"informacije si oglejte <ulink url=\"http://community.kde.org/Amarok/"
"Development/Scripting_HowTo_2.0\">Script-Writing-Howto</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6782
#, no-c-format
msgid "How do I manually change a track's score?"
msgstr "Kako ročno spremenim oceno skladbe?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6783
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You may change the score manually in the <guilabel>Track Details</guilabel> "
"dialog, available by right-clicking on a track, choosing <guilabel>Edit "
"Track Details</guilabel> and going to the <guilabel>Summary</guilabel> tab."
msgstr ""
"Rezultat lahko ročno spremenite v pogovornem oknu <guilabel>Podrobnosti "
"skladbe</guilabel>, ki je na voljo tako, da z desno tipko miške kliknete "
"skladbo, izberete <guilabel>Uredi podrobnosti skladbe</guilabel> in odprete "
"<guilabel>Povzetek</guilabel > zavihek."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6786
#, no-c-format
msgid "But I also want that stars system like in other players!"
msgstr "Želim pa tudi tisti sistem zvezdic kot pri drugih igralcih!"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6787
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&amarok;, of course, supports a user-defined rating system, and you can rate "
"your tracks with a single click using the <guilabel>Current Track</guilabel> "
"applet. You can also do this in the context menu (right-click) "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Edit Track Details</guimenu><guimenuitem>Summary</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> tab. If you have the rating stars displayed in "
"your playlist layout, you can also edit there, with the <emphasis>slow "
"double-click</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"&amarok; seveda podpira sistem ocenjevanja, ki ga določi uporabnik, in svoje "
"skladbe lahko ocenite z enim samim klikom z uporabo programčka "
"<guilabel>Trenutna skladba</guilabel>. To lahko storite tudi v kontekstnem "
"meniju (desni klik) <menuchoice><guimenu>Urejanje podrobnosti skladbe</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Povzetek</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Če imate v "
"postavitvi seznama predvajanja prikazane ocenjevalne zvezdice, jih lahko "
"urejate tudi tam s <emphasis>počasnim dvojnim klikom</emphasis>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6790
#, no-c-format
msgid "Can I drag and drop Plasma applets from the main window to the Desktop?"
msgstr ""
"Ali lahko povlečem in spustim programčke Plasma iz glavnega okna na namizje?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6791
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"No, but there are several Plasmoids available for your Desktop, which will "
"let you display information provided by &amarok; as well as control &amarok;."
msgstr ""
"Ne, vendar je za vaše namizje na voljo več plazmoidov, ki vam omogočajo "
"prikaz informacij, ki jih ponuja &amarok; kot tudi nadzor &amarok;."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6794
#, no-c-format
msgid "How can I save a stream?"
msgstr "Kako lahko shranim tok?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6795
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First of all, load the stream into the playlist. There are several ways to "
"do this: downloading the file and opening it with &amarok;; using the menu "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Playlist</guimenu><guimenuitem>Add stream</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>; among others."
msgstr ""
"Najprej naložite tok na seznam predvajanja. To lahko storite na več načinov: "
"s prenosom datoteke in odpiranjem z &amarok;; z uporabo menija "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Seznam predvajanja</guimenu><guimenuitem>Dodaj tok</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>; med ostalimi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6797
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Once the stream is loaded, you can save it by clicking on "
"<inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"Icon-document-save.png"
"\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> in the "
"<guilabel>Playlist</guilabel> pane, and giving it a meaningful name. The "
"Stream will then be added to the <guilabel>Saved Playlists</guilabel> view "
"for later reference."
msgstr ""
"Ko je tok naložen, ga lahko shranite s klikom na <inlinemediaobject> "
"<imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"Icon-document-save.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> "
"</imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> v podokno <guilabel>Playlist</guilabel> "
"in mu dajte smiselno ime. Tok bo nato dodan v pogled <guilabel>Shranjeni "
"seznami predvajanja</guilabel> za kasnejšo uporabo."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6800
#, no-c-format
msgid "Where do I find the settings for Amarok?"
msgstr "Kje najdem nastavitve za Amarok?"

#. Tag: userinput
#: index.docbook:6801
#, no-c-format
msgid "`kde4-config --localprefix`/share/apps/amarok"
msgstr "`kde4-config --localprefix`/share/apps/amarok"

#. Tag: userinput
#: index.docbook:6803
#, no-c-format
msgid "`kde4-config --localprefix`/share/config/amarokrc"
msgstr "`kde4-config --localprefix`/share/config/amarokrc"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6808
#, no-c-format
msgid "How can I obtain a backtrace?"
msgstr "Kako lahko pridobim povratno sled?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6809
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If &amarok; has crashed and you want to report it, visit the <ulink url="
"\"http://community.kde.org/Amarok/Development/DebuggingHowTo\">Debugging "
"HowTo</ulink>. The bug report must be made in <ulink url=\"http://bugs.kde."
"org\">bugs.kde.org</ulink> after verifying if it has not already been "
"reported."
msgstr ""
"Če &amarok; se je zrušil in želite to prijaviti, obiščite <ulink url="
"\"http://community.kde.org/Amarok/Development/DebuggingHowTo\">Debugging "
"HowTo</ulink>. Poročilo o napaki je treba narediti v <ulink url=\"http://"
"bugs.kde.org\">bugs.kde.org</ulink> po preverjanju, če ni bilo že "
"prijavljeno."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6812
#, no-c-format
msgid "Amarok just freezes! How can I help get this fixed?"
msgstr "Amarok samo zmrzne! Kako lahko pomagam, da se to popravi?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6813
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can obtain a backtrace of a frozen instance of &amarok; using gdb like "
"so:"
msgstr ""
"Pridobite lahko povratno sled zamrznjenega primerka &amarok; z uporabo gdb "
"takole:"

#. Tag: userinput
#: index.docbook:6815
#, no-c-format
msgid "$ gdb -p `pidof amarok` (gdb) thread apply full bt all"
msgstr "$ gdb -p nit `pidof amarok` (gdb) uporabi celotno bt vse"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6818
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Then just post the backtrace to <ulink url=\"http://paste.kde.org/"
"\">PasteBin</ulink>, as described in the <ulink url=\"http://community.kde."
"org/Amarok/Development/DebuggingHowTo\">Debugging HowTo</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Nato samo objavite povratno sled v <ulink url=\"http://paste.kde.org/"
"\">PasteBin</ulink>, kot je opisano v <ulink url=\"http://community.kde.org/"
"Amarok/ Development/DebuggingHowTo\">Navodila za odpravljanje napak</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6821
#, no-c-format
msgid "Amarok takes a lot of time to start"
msgstr "Amarok potrebuje veliko časa za zagon"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6822
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this happens you have to check what scripts you have installed and what "
"internet services are running, because some of them may slow down the "
"startup. Also, if you have streams in the playlist when you open &amarok;, "
"the startup can take a little longer. The same happens if you have a great "
"number of tracks in the playlist (over 300 and more)."
msgstr ""
"Če se to zgodi, morate preveriti, katere skripte imate nameščene in katere "
"internetne storitve se izvajajo, saj lahko nekatere od njih upočasnijo "
"zagon. Če imate tokove na seznamu predvajanja, ko odprete &amarok;, lahko "
"zagon traja nekoliko dlje. Enako se zgodi, če imate na seznamu predvajanja "
"veliko skladb (več kot 300 in več)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6824
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On the other hand, if you don't use KDE, but a different desktop "
"environment, startup time can be increased very slightly because there are "
"more libraries to be loaded."
msgstr ""
"Po drugi strani, če ne uporabljate KDE, ampak drugo namizno okolje, se lahko "
"čas zagona zelo malo podaljša, ker je treba naložiti več knjižnic."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6828
#, no-c-format
msgid "Development questions"
msgstr "Razvojna vprašanja"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6829
#, no-c-format
msgid "How do I get a GIT version of Amarok?"
msgstr "Kako dobim GIT različico Amaroka?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6830
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See the <ulink url=\"http://community.kde.org/Amarok/Development/"
"Development_HowTo\">Amarok Development build</ulink> instruction page. Check "
"here for a local build: <ulink url=\"http://blogs.fsfe.org/myriam/2009/09/"
"compiling-amarok-from-git-locally-full-summary/\">Building from Git Locally: "
"Full Summary</ulink>"
msgstr ""
"Oglejte si stran z navodili <ulink url=\"http://community.kde.org/Amarok/"
"Development/Development_HowTo\">Amarok Development build</ulink>. Preverite "
"tukaj za lokalno zgradbo: <ulink url=\"http://blogs.fsfe.org/myriam/2009/09/"
"compiling-amarok-from-git-locally-full-summary/\">Lokalna izdelava iz Git: "
"polno Povzetek</ulink>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6833
#, no-c-format
msgid "Why isn't Amarok part of KDE Multimedia?"
msgstr "Zakaj Amarok ni del KDE Multimedia?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6834
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Packages in the KDE Software Compilation proper have a release schedule that "
"doesn't fit with &amarok;'s development pace, and since none of the other "
"KDE applications depend on &amarok; there is no need to follow this release "
"schedule."
msgstr ""
"Paketi v kompilaciji programske opreme KDE imajo razpored izdaj, ki se ne "
"ujema s hitrostjo razvoja &amarok; in ker nobena druga aplikacija KDE ni "
"odvisna od &amarok; ni treba slediti temu urniku izdaje."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6837
#, no-c-format
msgid "I've found a bug / I've got a great idea for Amarok!"
msgstr "Našel sem napako / imam odlično idejo za Amarok!"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6838
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Please report it at <ulink url=\"http://bugs.kde.org/enter_bug.cgi?"
"product=amarok\">bugs.kde.org</ulink>. If you have a list of suggestions or "
"wishes it may be best to send them to our mailing list: <ulink url=\"mailto:"
"amarok@kde.org\">amarok@kde.org</ulink>. Simply posting the idea to our IRC "
"channels or on an obscure wiki page or blog won't help much as the "
"information will get lost."
msgstr ""
"Prijavite ga na <ulink url=\"http://bugs.kde.org/enter_bug.cgi?product=amarok"
"\">bugs.kde.org</ulink>. Če imate seznam predlogov ali želja, je morda "
"najbolje, da jih pošljete na naš poštni seznam: <ulink url=\"mailto:"
"amarok@kde.org\">amarok@kde.org</ulink>. Enostavna objava ideje na naših "
"kanalih IRC ali na neznani wiki strani ali blogu ne bo veliko pomagala, saj "
"se bodo informacije izgubile."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6841
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do you accept patches?"
msgstr "Ali sprejemate popravke?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6842
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Happily! Your best course of action is to let us know what you plan to do "
"before you do any work so we can discuss it, but don't fret; we haven't "
"turned down a patch yet! Discussion is mostly to help you patch the correct "
"bits of &amarok;. Submit your patches and code contributions to git."
"reviewboard.kde.org. See also <ulink url=\"http://blogs.fsfe.org/"
"myriam/2010/09/how-to-submit-patches-for-amarok/\">How to Submit Patches to "
"&amarok;</ulink>. If you have a bug fix then just go ahead; this is open "
"source after all."
msgstr ""
"Srečno! Vaš najboljši način ukrepanja je, da nam sporočite, kaj nameravate "
"narediti, preden se lotite kakršnega koli dela, da se lahko o tem "
"pogovorimo, vendar ne skrbite; še nismo zavrnili popravka! Razprava je "
"namenjena predvsem temu, da vam pomaga popraviti prave dele &amarok;a. "
"Pošljite svoje popravke in prispevke kode na git.reviewboard.kde.org. Glejte "
"tudi <ulink url=\"http://blogs.fsfe.org/myriam/2010/09/how-to-submit-patches-"
"for-amarok/\">Kako predložiti popravke v &amarok;</ulink>. Če imate popravek "
"napake, kar nadaljujte; navsezadnje je to odprta koda."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:6845
#, no-c-format
msgid "Why did you choose the name Amarok?"
msgstr "Zakaj ste izbrali ime Amarok?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:6846
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Amarok</emphasis> is an album by British composer Mike Oldfield. "
"Project founder Mark Kretschmann happens to like it a lot, and he thought "
"the name had a nice sound. Plus, of course, it contains the all important "
"<guilabel>K</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Amarok</emphasis> je album britanskega skladatelja Mika Oldfielda. "
"Ustanovitelju projekta Marku Kretschmannu je bilo zelo všeč in mislil je, da "
"ime lepo zveni. Poleg tega seveda vsebuje vse pomembne <guilabel>K</"
"guilabel>."

